1
00:00:05,094 --> 00:00:07,914
(The third night, filled with all kinds
of emotions, comes to an end.)

2
00:00:09,065 --> 00:00:15,504
(The Yeon House welcomes
the fourth morning.)

3
00:00:15,505 --> 00:00:17,005
(Jun Han and Ju Hee's Love Room)

4
00:00:17,006 --> 00:00:20,308
- Good morning.
- Right. They spent the night together!

5
00:00:20,543 --> 00:00:21,776
"Spent the night together?"

6
00:00:21,945 --> 00:00:24,345
(Happy)

7
00:00:24,814 --> 00:00:26,348
Wasn't it too hot while you were sleeping?

8
00:00:26,782 --> 00:00:27,548
No.

9
00:00:29,352 --> 00:00:31,220
They're giving off serious newlywed vibes.

10
00:00:31,221 --> 00:00:32,654
Right,
especially in those matching pajamas.

11
00:00:32,655 --> 00:00:33,655
How was my snoring?

12
00:00:35,324 --> 00:00:36,491
It wasn't that bad.

13
00:00:37,893 --> 00:00:39,927
That's a relief.

14
00:00:40,696 --> 00:00:41,996
You don't look puffy at all this morning.

15
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:45,300
But I feel puffy.

16
00:00:46,769 --> 00:00:47,896
No. Your eyes look nice and bright.

17
00:00:49,538 --> 00:00:51,506
(Squirming)

18
00:00:51,507 --> 00:00:52,373
I don't want to get out of bed.

19
00:00:52,742 --> 00:00:53,942
Oh, my.

20
00:00:56,645 --> 00:00:57,712
Why is it so hot in here?

21
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:01,583
Gosh.

22
00:01:01,584 --> 00:01:02,917
We spent the night together.

23
00:01:04,286 --> 00:01:05,853
Please don't put it that way.

24
00:01:07,356 --> 00:01:08,156
Oh, my gosh.

25
00:01:08,157 --> 00:01:09,357
I know, okay?

26
00:01:09,358 --> 00:01:11,626
We're even wearing matching pajamas.

27
00:01:15,097 --> 00:01:16,230
What's gotten into you?

28
00:01:16,231 --> 00:01:18,366
Ju Hee seems embarrassed.

29
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:19,934
Of course, she is.

30
00:01:19,935 --> 00:01:21,269
(Reading the room)

31
00:01:23,706 --> 00:01:25,440
I seriously think I'm a bit puffy.

32
00:01:26,075 --> 00:01:27,108
You're not. Not at all.

33
00:01:27,443 --> 00:01:29,043
I don't believe you.

34
00:01:31,547 --> 00:01:33,181
(Jun Han gets up too.)

35
00:01:33,182 --> 00:01:33,982
Gosh.

36
00:01:36,352 --> 00:01:37,686
(Checking his abs)

37
00:01:40,189 --> 00:01:41,022
We should get going, right?

38
00:01:41,290 --> 00:01:42,123
Yes.

39
00:01:45,594 --> 00:01:47,695
It's going to be
so awkward facing everyone.

40
00:01:48,864 --> 00:01:50,731
I'm just going out looking like this.

41
00:01:51,167 --> 00:01:52,667
(Laughing)

42
00:01:52,668 --> 00:01:53,735
I look pretty cool, no?

43
00:01:54,303 --> 00:01:55,270
Your hair?

44
00:01:55,271 --> 00:01:56,170
Well...

45
00:01:56,171 --> 00:01:57,005
He looks cute.

46
00:01:57,006 --> 00:01:58,206
You look like a cartoon character.

47
00:01:58,516 --> 00:01:59,862
You look like a manhwa character.

48
00:01:59,863 --> 00:02:02,009
(A morning full of mixed emotions
for the clueless Jun Han and Ju Hee.)

49
00:02:02,511 --> 00:02:04,479
(Jin Young and Yun So's Love Room)

50
00:02:04,547 --> 00:02:05,881
(Yun So starts the morning...)

51
00:02:05,882 --> 00:02:07,249
(by styling Jin Young's hair.)

52
00:02:07,783 --> 00:02:08,483
I think this will work.

53
00:02:09,285 --> 00:02:10,719
I can't do it while standing.

54
00:02:12,888 --> 00:02:15,289
He's doing her hair? That's so...

55
00:02:15,591 --> 00:02:16,558
Isn't he flirting?

56
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:18,559
Isn't that something couples do?

57
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,528
No. He's a hairstylist.

58
00:02:20,529 --> 00:02:21,596
- He's a hair designer.
- Oh, right.

59
00:02:22,932 --> 00:02:24,733
- That's right.
- He is a hair designer.

60
00:02:24,734 --> 00:02:26,134
(Don't forget. Yun So is a hair designer.)

61
00:02:27,303 --> 00:02:30,705
(Focused)

62
00:02:31,574 --> 00:02:33,041
You're such a professional.

63
00:02:33,309 --> 00:02:35,610
This is what it's like dating
a hair designer.

64
00:02:37,513 --> 00:02:38,813
How much volume do you want?

65
00:02:39,415 --> 00:02:42,283
Just do whatever you think looks best.

66
00:02:45,521 --> 00:02:46,454
I think it looks good already.

67
00:02:46,455 --> 00:02:47,422
- Really?
- Yes.

68
00:02:48,157 --> 00:02:49,657
You're going to spray it later, right?

69
00:02:50,726 --> 00:02:51,626
Spray it for me.

70
00:02:52,561 --> 00:02:53,961
Take a look. Do you like it?

71
00:02:55,064 --> 00:02:56,798
- Oh, my.
- I think it's perfect.

72
00:02:56,799 --> 00:02:58,299
(Surprised)

73
00:03:00,836 --> 00:03:01,869
- I love it.
- Do you?

74
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:02,670
I love it.

75
00:03:03,139 --> 00:03:03,839
It's great.

76
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:05,207
Perfect.

77
00:03:05,208 --> 00:03:06,181
I need to look from this angle.

78
00:03:06,509 --> 00:03:08,176
All right. You look beautiful.

79
00:03:08,177 --> 00:03:11,112
Make sure you tell everyone
I did your hair.

80
00:03:11,113 --> 00:03:12,180
I love it!

81
00:03:13,782 --> 00:03:15,216
It looks so natural.

82
00:03:16,118 --> 00:03:18,352
Don't they look so much closer now?
They seem really comfortable together.

83
00:03:18,353 --> 00:03:21,489
(Jin Young and Yun So have grown
much closer overnight.)

84
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:25,426
(Jin Woo sits in front
of the mirror first today, as always.)

85
00:03:26,595 --> 00:03:27,729
(Touching up)

86
00:03:27,730 --> 00:03:29,430
Jin Woo really looks like an idol.

87
00:03:29,431 --> 00:03:31,432
(He's getting ready for his date.)

88
00:03:32,768 --> 00:03:33,835
- Jin Woo.
- Yes?

89
00:03:36,105 --> 00:03:37,372
- Jun Han.
- Yes?

90
00:03:37,373 --> 00:03:39,641
(Jun Han returns from the Love Room
with a spring in his step.)

91
00:03:40,576 --> 00:03:42,110
How was last night with Ju Hee?

92
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:45,546
I said I was going
to make my feelings obvious.

93
00:03:46,482 --> 00:03:47,482
- To Ju Hee?
- Yes.

94
00:03:50,486 --> 00:03:51,553
I told her something yesterday.

95
00:03:53,989 --> 00:03:56,190
That I wanted...

96
00:03:56,959 --> 00:03:58,126
to seriously get to know...

97
00:03:59,094 --> 00:04:00,327
someone...

98
00:04:01,397 --> 00:04:02,697
as a potential partner.

99
00:04:03,966 --> 00:04:05,533
You mean just one or two people
instead of everyone?

100
00:04:05,901 --> 00:04:07,702
No, just Ju Hee.

101
00:04:07,703 --> 00:04:08,636
- Only her?
- Yes.

102
00:04:08,637 --> 00:04:10,304
Did it mean that much to you?

103
00:04:10,606 --> 00:04:11,639
I mean, spending time with her?

104
00:04:12,141 --> 00:04:12,942
Yes.

105
00:04:13,443 --> 00:04:16,110
I'd always wanted to go
in a jacuzzi with my girlfriend.

106
00:04:16,612 --> 00:04:18,313
I'd also never worn
matching pajamas before.

107
00:04:18,314 --> 00:04:20,315
So lying in bed together
wearing matching pajamas...

108
00:04:20,683 --> 00:04:22,917
felt really special.

109
00:04:24,119 --> 00:04:26,587
It felt like...

110
00:04:27,055 --> 00:04:29,223
we were a real couple traveling together.

111
00:04:29,992 --> 00:04:32,994
Do you think
you would've felt the same way...

112
00:04:32,995 --> 00:04:34,395
if you'd been with Jin Young or Ji Hye?

113
00:04:36,165 --> 00:04:38,333
If it had been Jin Young,
my feelings would've been crystal clear.

114
00:04:38,334 --> 00:04:39,734
I would've gone all in on her.

115
00:04:40,436 --> 00:04:41,569
But yesterday,

116
00:04:42,204 --> 00:04:43,137
Jin Young...

117
00:04:43,806 --> 00:04:45,106
confused me.

118
00:04:45,407 --> 00:04:47,141
And that really bothered me.

119
00:04:47,142 --> 00:04:49,777
I always distance myself
from people who leave me confused.

120
00:04:51,614 --> 00:04:54,417
So you like women
who are straightforward with you?

121
00:04:54,418 --> 00:04:55,250
Exactly.

122
00:04:56,518 --> 00:04:58,019
I don't like mixed signals.

123
00:04:58,721 --> 00:05:00,556
And Ju Hee made a huge gesture...

124
00:05:00,557 --> 00:05:02,924
by using that incredibly
valuable opportunity on you.

125
00:05:02,992 --> 00:05:04,492
- That meant a lot to you?
- Yes.

126
00:05:08,764 --> 00:05:11,599
She's even better than I expected.

127
00:05:13,936 --> 00:05:15,270
I really want to get
to know her seriously.

128
00:05:15,271 --> 00:05:16,438
(He wants to get to know Ju Hee better.)

129
00:05:16,463 --> 00:05:17,296
It's already the fourth day.

130
00:05:18,307 --> 00:05:19,974
He really falls fast.

131
00:05:21,343 --> 00:05:23,678
That's the charm of dating a younger guy.

132
00:05:23,912 --> 00:05:25,980
Exactly. If a younger guy
overthought everything,

133
00:05:25,981 --> 00:05:27,648
I'd probably find that unattractive.

134
00:05:27,983 --> 00:05:30,518
(Meanwhile, Yun So returns to his room.)

135
00:05:30,519 --> 00:05:31,452
Everyone was shocked.

136
00:05:32,054 --> 00:05:33,454
- Why?
- Because you picked Jin Young.

137
00:05:33,922 --> 00:05:34,788
Really?

138
00:05:36,725 --> 00:05:37,858
I guess no one expected it.

139
00:05:37,859 --> 00:05:39,927
Right. No one knows...

140
00:05:40,329 --> 00:05:41,896
- unless you tell them.
- I'd been telling...

141
00:05:41,997 --> 00:05:44,198
everyone I was interested in Ju Hee.

142
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:46,200
- Exactly.
- Me taking Jin Young...

143
00:05:48,704 --> 00:05:50,905
How was it? Has your attraction grown?

144
00:05:52,841 --> 00:05:53,708
(Grinning)

145
00:05:53,709 --> 00:05:56,243
What is it? You're not sure?

146
00:05:56,945 --> 00:05:59,246
We've definitely gotten closer, yes.

147
00:05:59,247 --> 00:06:00,347
- Of course.
- But...

148
00:06:01,084 --> 00:06:03,418
I'm still not sure
if I'm attracted to her.

149
00:06:04,753 --> 00:06:05,586
I honestly don't know.

150
00:06:05,787 --> 00:06:07,588
- Oh, boy.
- That's interesting.

151
00:06:07,589 --> 00:06:10,524
(Ju Hee, Jin Young,
and Ji Hye's Powder Room)

152
00:06:10,693 --> 00:06:11,526
How was it?

153
00:06:12,795 --> 00:06:13,795
It was fun.

154
00:06:15,597 --> 00:06:18,499
Is he talkative? I didn't think he was.

155
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:22,403
He's not especially talkative,
but he's not quiet either.

156
00:06:23,172 --> 00:06:24,606
So, Jin Young,

157
00:06:24,607 --> 00:06:27,442
are Jun Han and Jung Won
the only two you're interested in?

158
00:06:28,711 --> 00:06:32,781
I'm not even 100 percent sure
about Jun Han yet.

159
00:06:33,148 --> 00:06:34,482
(Glancing)

160
00:06:36,985 --> 00:06:37,952
Can you move over a little?

161
00:06:38,821 --> 00:06:45,795
(Jin Young and Ji Hye clash
over Jung Won during the Truth Game.)

162
00:06:46,729 --> 00:06:52,033
(The subtle tension between them continues
from yesterday.)

163
00:06:52,735 --> 00:06:57,372
(Jin Young finishes getting ready first
and leaves the powder room.)

164
00:06:57,373 --> 00:06:59,240
Something must be bothering her.

165
00:06:59,241 --> 00:07:01,710
(Unsure)

166
00:07:02,444 --> 00:07:03,511
You know...

167
00:07:06,615 --> 00:07:08,783
My conversation
with him last night was so boring.

168
00:07:09,118 --> 00:07:11,986
- Oh, my gosh!
- With Jun Han.

169
00:07:12,155 --> 00:07:13,454
Really? I thought he was interesting.

170
00:07:14,022 --> 00:07:15,789
Didn't you say he was fun?

171
00:07:16,191 --> 00:07:18,425
I think he's just shy around new people,

172
00:07:18,426 --> 00:07:20,628
but once he gets comfortable...

173
00:07:21,029 --> 00:07:22,863
You think Jun Han is shy
around new people?

174
00:07:22,864 --> 00:07:23,831
- Yes.
- Oh, really?

175
00:07:23,832 --> 00:07:24,598
Yes.

176
00:07:24,599 --> 00:07:26,400
I've barely talked to him,

177
00:07:26,869 --> 00:07:28,636
so I never noticed.

178
00:07:29,772 --> 00:07:32,073
To me, he always seemed cheerful and fun.

179
00:07:32,074 --> 00:07:33,674
I know. He's always so outgoing...

180
00:07:33,675 --> 00:07:36,411
when everyone's around.
That's why I was curious.

181
00:07:36,579 --> 00:07:38,846
But once we were alone together,
he became so awkward.

182
00:07:38,847 --> 00:07:41,115
I figured he was just shy
because it was unfamiliar.

183
00:07:41,116 --> 00:07:42,951
But yesterday, the two of us were...

184
00:07:42,952 --> 00:07:45,653
a complete awkward mess.

185
00:07:46,655 --> 00:07:48,256
He doesn't seem like that at all.

186
00:07:49,057 --> 00:07:50,824
He was extremely awkward.

187
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:54,595
I couldn't help thinking
he was just a kid.

188
00:07:54,596 --> 00:07:56,531
You might be right.

189
00:07:57,433 --> 00:07:58,493
- And...
- That actually makes sense.

190
00:07:58,534 --> 00:08:00,668
there were so many things
he's never done before.

191
00:08:00,803 --> 00:08:02,704
- Really?
- He kept bringing them up.

192
00:08:03,338 --> 00:08:06,040
He said he'd always wanted
to go in a jacuzzi with his girlfriend.

193
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,508
But actually, I felt so sorry for him.

194
00:08:11,881 --> 00:08:13,247
I genuinely felt bad.

195
00:08:13,248 --> 00:08:15,517
Then he said he'd never worn
matching pajamas before.

196
00:08:15,518 --> 00:08:16,851
And I felt sorry for him all over again.

197
00:08:16,852 --> 00:08:18,653
Really? Gosh.

198
00:08:18,654 --> 00:08:19,387
Yes!

199
00:08:19,388 --> 00:08:21,355
(Can I share this experience
without attaching much meaning to it?)

200
00:08:21,356 --> 00:08:24,725
Maybe he's just never dated someone
who's very romantic before.

201
00:08:25,194 --> 00:08:28,897
But I don't like taking
the lead in a relationship,

202
00:08:28,898 --> 00:08:31,065
and that's exactly how he made me feel.

203
00:08:32,835 --> 00:08:33,835
- That's understandable.
- So...

204
00:08:35,070 --> 00:08:39,573
I expected him to be a little more manly.

205
00:08:40,475 --> 00:08:42,643
I'm honestly a little flustered.

206
00:08:44,913 --> 00:08:45,813
That's so unexpected.

207
00:08:45,814 --> 00:08:49,583
- And I thought...
- I thought you two had a great time.

208
00:08:49,584 --> 00:08:53,354
We did have a good time,

209
00:08:54,122 --> 00:08:57,391
but not in the way I'd expected.

210
00:08:59,328 --> 00:09:04,265
(Jun Han and Ju Hee are
unfortunately on different wavelengths.)

211
00:09:04,266 --> 00:09:05,985
It was exciting for Jun Han
because it was his first time,

212
00:09:05,986 --> 00:09:07,702
but it only made Ju Hee feel pressured.

213
00:09:07,703 --> 00:09:09,137
(What thrilled him felt
like pressure to Ju Hee.)

214
00:09:09,271 --> 00:09:10,605
So you're not curious about him anymore?

215
00:09:11,106 --> 00:09:12,706
I don't think I am.

216
00:09:13,675 --> 00:09:16,677
He said he likes things to be clear.

217
00:09:17,079 --> 00:09:18,112
So I think I should tell him honestly.

218
00:09:20,582 --> 00:09:24,084
So you've already made up your mind?

219
00:09:25,521 --> 00:09:26,654
I don't know what I should do.

220
00:09:27,155 --> 00:09:29,022
I'm not saying
I've completely made up my mind.

221
00:09:30,025 --> 00:09:31,158
It's driving me crazy.

222
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:36,964
(The date only leaves
Ju Hee more conflicted.)

223
00:09:37,699 --> 00:09:41,168
(Meanwhile, Jun Han is talking
with Si Won.)

224
00:09:41,570 --> 00:09:42,372
What do you think?

225
00:09:43,079 --> 00:09:43,971
This is fun, isn't it?

226
00:09:44,507 --> 00:09:46,807
I had so much fun playing
that game last night.

227
00:09:47,743 --> 00:09:49,844
I was feeling really down.

228
00:09:49,845 --> 00:09:51,446
But the moment she picked me,

229
00:09:51,447 --> 00:09:52,814
I got this huge dopamine rush.

230
00:09:53,315 --> 00:09:54,548
- No!
- That woke me right up.

231
00:09:54,549 --> 00:09:55,449
Exactly.

232
00:09:55,717 --> 00:09:57,619
After that,

233
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:59,621
I was on a high.

234
00:09:59,622 --> 00:10:02,690
Especially while we were talking in bed.

235
00:10:03,797 --> 00:10:04,992
- With Ju Hee?
- Yes.

236
00:10:05,821 --> 00:10:08,154
I couldn't calm down even until then.

237
00:10:08,864 --> 00:10:10,064
Really?

238
00:10:10,064 --> 00:10:11,231
- You must've had a lot of fun.
- Yes.

239
00:10:11,231 --> 00:10:13,131
Jun Han seems a bit excited now.

240
00:10:13,397 --> 00:10:14,431
But I'm not sure.

241
00:10:15,331 --> 00:10:16,397
- Really?
- Here he comes.

242
00:10:16,397 --> 00:10:17,897
Yun So, no!

243
00:10:21,597 --> 00:10:23,497
It can change all of a sudden.

244
00:10:23,864 --> 00:10:25,031
Suddenly, it can change.

245
00:10:25,031 --> 00:10:25,997
That's true.

246
00:10:25,997 --> 00:10:27,164
(Glancing)

247
00:10:27,164 --> 00:10:27,931
He's glancing over.

248
00:10:30,031 --> 00:10:31,397
- Oh, dear.
- I'm heading out.

249
00:10:32,597 --> 00:10:33,397
I'm heading out.

250
00:10:34,731 --> 00:10:35,531
I'm off.

251
00:10:35,531 --> 00:10:37,431
(As Yun So appears,
they quickly end the conversation.)

252
00:10:42,897 --> 00:10:44,831
What did he say?

253
00:10:45,431 --> 00:10:46,397
He said he had a lot of fun.

254
00:10:46,831 --> 00:10:47,631
I see.

255
00:10:47,631 --> 00:10:48,764
(Throwing his phone)

256
00:10:49,697 --> 00:10:52,197
He said even talking in bed was fun.

257
00:10:52,864 --> 00:10:54,031
I didn't want to know that.

258
00:10:55,764 --> 00:10:57,597
It seems like he's going for Ju Hee.

259
00:10:57,597 --> 00:10:58,497
Ju Hee.

260
00:10:59,297 --> 00:11:00,864
- Is that so?
- I think so.

261
00:11:06,064 --> 00:11:07,531
Ju Hee is popular.

262
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:08,670
Yes.

263
00:11:10,397 --> 00:11:12,664
I feel like...

264
00:11:13,364 --> 00:11:14,831
she's not going to choose me.

265
00:11:14,831 --> 00:11:16,664
- Today?
- Yes.

266
00:11:17,464 --> 00:11:18,697
You never know.

267
00:11:19,064 --> 00:11:21,731
I feel like things are solid
between them now.

268
00:11:21,731 --> 00:11:22,664
Things must be good.

269
00:11:22,664 --> 00:11:23,431
Ju Hee?

270
00:11:23,864 --> 00:11:24,731
Really?

271
00:11:25,164 --> 00:11:26,031
Are you that sure?

272
00:11:27,764 --> 00:11:30,197
- I'll still do my best.
- Right.

273
00:11:30,631 --> 00:11:32,131
I think I'll have my answer today.

274
00:11:32,564 --> 00:11:33,597
About your feelings?

275
00:11:33,597 --> 00:11:34,364
Yes.

276
00:11:34,697 --> 00:11:37,464
She might try him and come back later.

277
00:11:37,464 --> 00:11:38,364
There's still a chance.

278
00:11:38,831 --> 00:11:40,931
I think today and tomorrow might be
the last chance.

279
00:11:40,931 --> 00:11:43,131
I hope Yun So stays strong.

280
00:11:43,597 --> 00:11:46,331
I'm so curious about Jun Han.

281
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:48,064
- Jun Han?
- Yes.

282
00:11:48,397 --> 00:11:49,997
How about talking to him?

283
00:11:50,431 --> 00:11:51,797
Honestly, I don't want to talk to him.

284
00:11:55,497 --> 00:11:57,731
(Jun Han and Jung Won are
in the common area.)

285
00:11:58,131 --> 00:12:01,964
Yun So and you are like...

286
00:12:02,231 --> 00:12:03,831
- Who?
- Yun So.

287
00:12:04,197 --> 00:12:05,197
- Yun So?
- Yes.

288
00:12:06,464 --> 00:12:09,064
I feel like Yun So is saying...

289
00:12:09,497 --> 00:12:11,931
- "Bring it on."
- Yes, "Bring it on."

290
00:12:11,931 --> 00:12:13,231
That's the vibe I get.

291
00:12:13,231 --> 00:12:14,664
Back to the pool.

292
00:12:14,664 --> 00:12:16,464
How is it going now? What do you think?

293
00:12:16,464 --> 00:12:17,331
- For me?
- Yes.

294
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:19,970
Once I choose someone in my mind,

295
00:12:21,164 --> 00:12:22,331
I won't lose.

296
00:12:23,764 --> 00:12:26,664
You'll have a serious showdown today.

297
00:12:26,664 --> 00:12:29,131
Right, but I don't lose.

298
00:12:29,631 --> 00:12:31,731
I like that.

299
00:12:33,697 --> 00:12:36,197
I don't want them to be in the same room.

300
00:12:36,197 --> 00:12:37,797
(Yun So is heading to the common area.)

301
00:12:37,964 --> 00:12:39,031
I'm nervous.

302
00:12:39,664 --> 00:12:40,664
(Glancing)

303
00:12:42,997 --> 00:12:44,297
(Turning his head)

304
00:12:48,197 --> 00:12:49,164
Good morning.

305
00:12:49,864 --> 00:12:51,264
Let's have a talk, just us guys.

306
00:12:51,631 --> 00:12:52,431
That's good.

307
00:12:53,931 --> 00:12:55,664
He threw that at him.

308
00:12:56,797 --> 00:13:01,031
(Jun Han and Yun So are
facing each other.)

309
00:13:01,897 --> 00:13:03,097
(Glancing over.)

310
00:13:03,097 --> 00:13:04,664
Let's eat together as guys.

311
00:13:05,197 --> 00:13:06,297
(Looking away)

312
00:13:06,564 --> 00:13:09,697
(Jun Han and Yun So seem awkward.)

313
00:13:10,497 --> 00:13:11,331
Do you want more meat?

314
00:13:11,331 --> 00:13:12,364
Why isn't Jung Won coming?

315
00:13:12,364 --> 00:13:13,397
Do we need more?

316
00:13:14,164 --> 00:13:15,931
- But...
- It's 400g.

317
00:13:15,931 --> 00:13:17,331
They're talking about random things.

318
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:20,231
- I'm good. I don't eat a lot.
- Is that okay? How about this much?

319
00:13:23,197 --> 00:13:25,097
- I hate it.
- I don't eat a lot in the morning.

320
00:13:29,531 --> 00:13:30,764
I don't eat a lot in the morning.

321
00:13:33,064 --> 00:13:35,664
Did you decide
who you're going after yesterday?

322
00:13:36,731 --> 00:13:37,631
He brought it up right away.

323
00:13:37,631 --> 00:13:38,464
A little bit.

324
00:13:41,131 --> 00:13:41,964
I see.

325
00:13:44,531 --> 00:13:47,297
You're not sure about it yet?

326
00:13:49,497 --> 00:13:50,597
I want to check again.

327
00:13:51,064 --> 00:13:52,664
I'm not totally sure,

328
00:13:53,331 --> 00:13:54,664
but 70 to 80 percent sure.

329
00:13:54,664 --> 00:13:55,997
- It's 70 to 80 percent?
- Yes.

330
00:13:57,064 --> 00:13:59,031
Are you saying you want
to go out with Ju Hee again?

331
00:13:59,631 --> 00:14:00,664
- Since yesterday.
- Yes.

332
00:14:00,664 --> 00:14:01,431
Yes.

333
00:14:03,864 --> 00:14:05,031
That's intense.

334
00:14:05,031 --> 00:14:08,897
(There's tension between them.)

335
00:14:12,031 --> 00:14:13,131
I got a message.

336
00:14:13,464 --> 00:14:14,264
You did?

337
00:14:15,731 --> 00:14:17,397
"In the common area's mailbox,"

338
00:14:17,397 --> 00:14:19,864
"cards with the men's hidden charms
have arrived."

339
00:14:19,864 --> 00:14:20,864
Hidden charms?

340
00:14:20,864 --> 00:14:22,931
To the mailbox by 11:40 a.m.?

341
00:14:22,931 --> 00:14:24,531
- By 11:40 a.m.?
- Yes.

342
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:27,331
To the common area by 11:40 a.m.

343
00:14:27,331 --> 00:14:29,997
(The men's hidden charms are
in the mailbox.)

344
00:14:31,664 --> 00:14:33,464
- Shall we take a look?
- Yes.

345
00:14:33,464 --> 00:14:35,131
The men's hidden charms.

346
00:14:35,131 --> 00:14:36,697
"Read each Charm Card..."

347
00:14:36,697 --> 00:14:38,964
"and pick one."

348
00:14:38,964 --> 00:14:42,331
("You'll go on a date with the person
the Charm Card belongs to.")

349
00:14:42,931 --> 00:14:44,231
It's a random date.

350
00:14:44,597 --> 00:14:45,564
You could guess who it is...

351
00:14:45,564 --> 00:14:47,764
or wouldn't know who it is at all.

352
00:14:47,764 --> 00:14:49,331
- The cards are random.
- Yes.

353
00:14:50,464 --> 00:14:53,364
(The younger men's hidden charms...)

354
00:14:53,364 --> 00:14:58,564
(are written on the cards in the mailbox.)

355
00:15:01,797 --> 00:15:04,464
(This morning)

356
00:15:05,597 --> 00:15:07,164
(The men wrote down their hidden charms.)

357
00:15:07,164 --> 00:15:08,564
They all wrote it down.

358
00:15:10,697 --> 00:15:13,797
(And they put the cards in the mailbox.)

359
00:15:15,031 --> 00:15:18,431
(What kinds of charms did they write?)

360
00:15:18,431 --> 00:15:19,397
I'm so curious...

361
00:15:19,397 --> 00:15:22,664
to know what they put
as their hidden charms.

362
00:15:23,064 --> 00:15:25,964
What if Jin Woo wrote,
"Actually, I'm a strong man."

363
00:15:27,131 --> 00:15:29,197
They probably left a clue...

364
00:15:29,197 --> 00:15:31,064
so the girls could tell who they are.

365
00:15:31,364 --> 00:15:33,631
The girls should read them carefully.

366
00:15:35,031 --> 00:15:36,364
What does it say?

367
00:15:36,997 --> 00:15:39,231
- Shall we read it out loud?
- "When we're together,"

368
00:15:39,231 --> 00:15:41,864
"I can make her happy
and show her a great time."

369
00:15:42,264 --> 00:15:43,764
That sounds like Jun Han.

370
00:15:43,764 --> 00:15:44,931
"I talk a lot."

371
00:15:44,931 --> 00:15:46,431
"I'm playful,"

372
00:15:46,431 --> 00:15:48,264
"and I'm a great listener."

373
00:15:48,264 --> 00:15:50,397
- "I talk a lot?"
- Talk a lot?

374
00:15:50,397 --> 00:15:51,897
Talk a lot?

375
00:15:51,897 --> 00:15:52,864
Jin Woo?

376
00:15:52,864 --> 00:15:54,497
(Who could it be?)

377
00:15:54,931 --> 00:15:57,131
"I don't change."

378
00:15:57,431 --> 00:15:58,397
Yun So!

379
00:15:59,831 --> 00:16:00,897
Yun So!

380
00:16:00,897 --> 00:16:01,864
Isn't that Jin Woo?

381
00:16:03,097 --> 00:16:06,697
- "Tough guy."
- "Tough guy."

382
00:16:08,297 --> 00:16:09,564
What about it?

383
00:16:10,864 --> 00:16:12,831
(While everyone was silent,
her true feelings came out.)

384
00:16:15,697 --> 00:16:17,797
Gentle guys always say they're tough guys.

385
00:16:17,797 --> 00:16:19,697
(Who is the tough guy
that made the girls laugh?)

386
00:16:20,297 --> 00:16:23,731
(That's the last younger man's
hidden charm?)

387
00:16:24,025 --> 00:16:25,364
("I'm a switcher: gentle by day,
wild at night")

388
00:16:25,364 --> 00:16:26,561
"Gentle by day, wild at night."

389
00:16:26,764 --> 00:16:27,897
Who put that?

390
00:16:27,897 --> 00:16:29,231
I'm so curious.

391
00:16:29,231 --> 00:16:30,631
I knew someone would put that.

392
00:16:31,597 --> 00:16:32,697
That's so funny.

393
00:16:32,697 --> 00:16:34,964
Who wrote, "Gentle by day, wild at night?"

394
00:16:34,964 --> 00:16:36,464
- I would never pick that.
- I knew it.

395
00:16:36,464 --> 00:16:37,364
I want that one.

396
00:16:37,364 --> 00:16:38,897
- Really?
- Who is it?

397
00:16:39,397 --> 00:16:40,331
I want that one.

398
00:16:40,331 --> 00:16:42,497
(Ji Hye chooses the switcher card
without hesitation.)

399
00:16:42,497 --> 00:16:43,464
It's cute.

400
00:16:44,197 --> 00:16:45,731
I knew it.

401
00:16:46,031 --> 00:16:47,431
(Why not?)

402
00:16:47,431 --> 00:16:51,564
I thought it'd be Jun Han.

403
00:16:51,564 --> 00:16:53,664
We haven't talked yet.

404
00:16:54,831 --> 00:16:59,264
(Ji Hye expressed her feelings
to Jung Won yesterday.)

405
00:16:59,531 --> 00:17:01,297
I thought...

406
00:17:01,297 --> 00:17:04,097
today might be the last chance.

407
00:17:04,097 --> 00:17:08,964
I've wanted to get to know him
at some point.

408
00:17:09,397 --> 00:17:13,397
I picked that,
wondering if it was Jun Han.

409
00:17:13,397 --> 00:17:14,697
(Is this Jun Han as Ji Hye expected?)

410
00:17:15,297 --> 00:17:20,231
(As Ji Hye picks her card quickly,
they start a battle of nerves.)

411
00:17:23,131 --> 00:17:24,264
I pick this, then.

412
00:17:26,031 --> 00:17:28,031
It's pretty normal.

413
00:17:29,197 --> 00:17:30,231
(The Charm Card that she chose)

414
00:17:30,231 --> 00:17:31,897
That sounds like Si Won.

415
00:17:32,431 --> 00:17:33,831
I looked at the cards...

416
00:17:33,831 --> 00:17:35,897
and couldn't tell
which one was Jung Won's.

417
00:17:35,897 --> 00:17:37,664
I just picked one that sounded like him.

418
00:17:39,031 --> 00:17:40,031
(The remaining cards)

419
00:17:40,031 --> 00:17:40,897
(I talk a lot and I'm playful.)

420
00:17:40,897 --> 00:17:41,964
(I don't change.)

421
00:17:41,964 --> 00:17:43,264
(Tough guy)

422
00:17:43,264 --> 00:17:44,331
I pick...

423
00:17:47,931 --> 00:17:48,897
I pick this one.

424
00:17:48,897 --> 00:17:50,297
- "I don't change?"
- Yes.

425
00:17:51,997 --> 00:17:54,964
I didn't really have anyone in mind.

426
00:17:54,964 --> 00:17:58,131
I just chose a charm...

427
00:17:58,131 --> 00:18:02,531
that seemed to align
with my relationship values.

428
00:18:02,531 --> 00:18:04,064
That's why I picked it.

429
00:18:04,397 --> 00:18:06,697
That card sounds like Yun So.

430
00:18:06,697 --> 00:18:07,831
(The remaining cards)

431
00:18:07,831 --> 00:18:08,797
(I talk a lot and I'm playful.)

432
00:18:08,797 --> 00:18:09,831
(Tough guy)

433
00:18:10,731 --> 00:18:13,764
(Thinking)

434
00:18:14,497 --> 00:18:15,631
I pick this.

435
00:18:15,631 --> 00:18:16,464
(Glancing)

436
00:18:16,464 --> 00:18:17,264
That's good.

437
00:18:18,564 --> 00:18:20,364
(The Charm Card that Yu Jin chose)

438
00:18:20,364 --> 00:18:21,331
I'm so curious.

439
00:18:22,864 --> 00:18:23,797
(Only one Charm Card is left.)

440
00:18:23,797 --> 00:18:25,497
So, Ju Hee picked "tough guy."

441
00:18:26,164 --> 00:18:29,231
(The Charm Card that Ju Hee chose)

442
00:18:29,597 --> 00:18:30,564
The last one.

443
00:18:32,397 --> 00:18:35,131
I had a lot going through my mind.

444
00:18:35,431 --> 00:18:40,397
I felt that I wanted to talk
to someone new,

445
00:18:40,764 --> 00:18:43,731
so I just waited until the end.

446
00:18:46,431 --> 00:18:48,297
(Who's the owner of the Charm Card
that Ju Hee picked?)

447
00:18:48,297 --> 00:18:49,797
Who could it be?

448
00:18:51,264 --> 00:18:52,231
"Tough guy."

449
00:18:53,531 --> 00:18:55,631
I feel like this is Jin Woo.

450
00:18:55,631 --> 00:18:58,697
I remember he kept saying
he was a tough guy.

451
00:18:59,031 --> 00:19:00,731
(I think I know who that is.)

452
00:19:01,097 --> 00:19:04,864
I remember Jin Woo saying
he was a tough guy.

453
00:19:05,197 --> 00:19:09,597
So I thought that card could
belong to him.

454
00:19:10,997 --> 00:19:12,464
(Their first day meeting)

455
00:19:12,731 --> 00:19:14,364
I'm okay. I'm a tough guy.

456
00:19:15,190 --> 00:19:18,424
I think personality-wise, I'm a tough guy.

457
00:19:20,131 --> 00:19:22,731
He mentioned that a lot.

458
00:19:23,397 --> 00:19:24,431
That must be Jin Woo.

459
00:19:24,431 --> 00:19:25,531
(It could be Jin Woo.)

460
00:19:26,197 --> 00:19:28,197
Jin Woo wants to be funny,

461
00:19:28,197 --> 00:19:31,331
so he would've tried to sound funny.

462
00:19:32,097 --> 00:19:34,131
What if "Gentle by day,
wild at night" is Jin Woo?

463
00:19:35,497 --> 00:19:38,864
- Either of them must be Jin Woo.
- I think either card belongs to Jin Woo.

464
00:19:39,131 --> 00:19:40,097
Everyone says that's Jin Woo.

465
00:19:40,097 --> 00:19:42,764
(These are charms we don't expect
from Jin Woo.)

466
00:19:43,034 --> 00:19:46,064
I thought Yun So would be
either of these cards.

467
00:19:46,064 --> 00:19:48,397
If it's Yun So, that would be a mess.

468
00:19:48,797 --> 00:19:50,364
We're really not close.

469
00:19:51,097 --> 00:19:55,131
- None of us are close to Yun So.
- We're not close to him.

470
00:19:55,564 --> 00:19:57,897
He seems funny.

471
00:19:58,497 --> 00:20:00,931
The guys must be nervous,

472
00:20:00,931 --> 00:20:02,931
- wondering who's going out with them.
- Wondering who's coming.

473
00:20:02,931 --> 00:20:04,831
They might hope to see someone specific.

474
00:20:04,859 --> 00:20:06,660
Or it could be someone else.

475
00:20:06,661 --> 00:20:07,961
(Which guy will the women go
on a date with?)

476
00:20:08,129 --> 00:20:10,463
- Have a great time on your dates!
- See you.

477
00:20:10,464 --> 00:20:12,366
- See you.
- See you later.

478
00:20:13,735 --> 00:20:15,802
- Bye.
- Bye.

479
00:20:21,409 --> 00:20:25,646
(With the Charm Cards they chose,)

480
00:20:26,614 --> 00:20:31,017
(the women are waiting
for the younger guys.)

481
00:20:31,786 --> 00:20:35,655
(Which younger guy will
get into their cars?)

482
00:20:36,958 --> 00:20:40,262
(The first younger guy to arrive
at the parking lot is Jin Woo.)

483
00:20:40,263 --> 00:20:41,295
It's Ji Woo!

484
00:20:43,398 --> 00:20:44,298
What will happen?

485
00:20:44,299 --> 00:20:45,866
(Which woman chose Jin Woo's Charm Card?)

486
00:20:46,234 --> 00:20:48,135
(Glancing)

487
00:20:48,536 --> 00:20:50,103
(Peeking)

488
00:20:51,172 --> 00:20:55,909
(The older women are nervous
as the younger guy appears.)

489
00:20:57,779 --> 00:20:59,847
(Which woman's car will he get into?)

490
00:20:59,848 --> 00:21:01,081
He's quite tough.

491
00:21:02,116 --> 00:21:04,818
(Is Jin Woo the tough guy
Ju Hee expected?)

492
00:21:05,119 --> 00:21:08,154
(Or will it be Ji Hye,
who picked the switcher card?)

493
00:21:08,155 --> 00:21:11,624
(Ju Hee, Ji Hye)

494
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:15,462
Of course,
I hoped my date would be Ji Hye,

495
00:21:15,463 --> 00:21:17,764
but I also thought it might not be her.

496
00:21:17,765 --> 00:21:19,866
The odds are 1 in 5.

497
00:21:19,968 --> 00:21:23,203
(Whose car will Jin Woo get into?)

498
00:21:24,339 --> 00:21:27,274
(All eyes are on him.)

499
00:21:27,275 --> 00:21:29,510
(Ju Hee, Ji Hye)

500
00:21:29,511 --> 00:21:32,112
(He walks past Ji Hee and Ji Hye...)

501
00:21:32,113 --> 00:21:34,715
(and heads toward another woman's car.)

502
00:21:34,716 --> 00:21:35,649
Hi.

503
00:21:35,650 --> 00:21:36,583
- Who is it?
- Who is it?

504
00:21:36,818 --> 00:21:37,951
Gosh!

505
00:21:37,952 --> 00:21:39,419
- Hi.
- Ji Seung?

506
00:21:39,787 --> 00:21:40,987
- What?
- You didn't know I was coming?

507
00:21:41,089 --> 00:21:41,989
No.

508
00:21:42,357 --> 00:21:43,190
It's me.

509
00:21:43,658 --> 00:21:45,425
- Gosh.
- You chose after you read the letter.

510
00:21:45,426 --> 00:21:46,560
- Right.
- Right?

511
00:21:46,561 --> 00:21:47,427
It's me.

512
00:21:47,829 --> 00:21:49,396
I didn't expect this.

513
00:21:49,897 --> 00:21:50,830
Who were you expecting?

514
00:21:50,831 --> 00:21:51,865
I wasn't expecting anyone.

515
00:21:51,866 --> 00:21:54,801
I just picked it because I liked it.

516
00:21:55,503 --> 00:21:56,536
I was really surprised.

517
00:21:56,804 --> 00:22:00,540
But I thought it was nice...

518
00:22:00,842 --> 00:22:02,944
to get a chance to talk to someone new.

519
00:22:04,212 --> 00:22:05,946
Besides Ji Hye, there were moments...

520
00:22:06,548 --> 00:22:11,651
when Ji Seung's mature, intelligent speech
felt attractive,

521
00:22:11,652 --> 00:22:15,688
so I thought it would be good
to talk with her as well.

522
00:22:17,358 --> 00:22:19,226
I thought you'd know my card.

523
00:22:19,227 --> 00:22:20,126
No way.

524
00:22:20,494 --> 00:22:22,496
I could guess it with another card.

525
00:22:22,497 --> 00:22:23,163
Which one?

526
00:22:23,164 --> 00:22:25,665
Things like the switcher card.

527
00:22:25,666 --> 00:22:28,602
Things that felt like a trickster
or a tough guy.

528
00:22:29,203 --> 00:22:31,137
I'm a bit different.

529
00:22:31,138 --> 00:22:33,306
I act a bit differently
when I'm 1-on-1 with a woman...

530
00:22:33,307 --> 00:22:35,341
compared to when there are people around.

531
00:22:36,044 --> 00:22:37,511
It's definitely different.

532
00:22:37,679 --> 00:22:40,113
- That's very funny.
- What kind of date will they have?

533
00:22:40,815 --> 00:22:42,516
(Sighing)

534
00:22:42,784 --> 00:22:47,354
I really believed
Jin Woo was the tough guy,

535
00:22:47,689 --> 00:22:48,789
but I guess I was wrong.

536
00:22:49,090 --> 00:22:51,291
Maybe Ju Hee was hoping for Jin Woo.

537
00:22:51,292 --> 00:22:55,095
(Who is the younger guy appealing
as the tough guy?)

538
00:22:55,596 --> 00:22:57,931
(The second younger man, Yun So)

539
00:22:57,932 --> 00:22:58,798
Oh, the tough guy!

540
00:23:00,401 --> 00:23:01,968
It's a new guy!

541
00:23:01,969 --> 00:23:03,303
(Could the tough guy be Yun So?)

542
00:23:06,007 --> 00:23:09,776
(Which lady chose Yun So's Charm Card?)

543
00:23:12,347 --> 00:23:13,781
(Hesitant)

544
00:23:14,615 --> 00:23:17,551
(Looking back)

545
00:23:17,552 --> 00:23:18,618
(Yu Jin, Ju Hee)

546
00:23:18,619 --> 00:23:21,654
(Yun So pauses
in front of Yu Jin's and Ju Hee's cars.)

547
00:23:22,857 --> 00:23:23,723
(Please.)

548
00:23:24,058 --> 00:23:24,924
No way.

549
00:23:25,593 --> 00:23:29,362
Could it be? No way.

550
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:34,602
Ju Hee seemed
a bit uncomfortable with Yun So.

551
00:23:34,603 --> 00:23:35,469
What's going on?

552
00:23:35,903 --> 00:23:37,570
(Full of curiosity)

553
00:23:38,439 --> 00:23:42,008
(Who picked Yun So's Charm Card,
Yu Jin or Ji Seung?)

554
00:23:45,546 --> 00:23:47,881
- It's Yu Jin!
- Yu Jin!

555
00:23:48,683 --> 00:23:49,616
Oh, my gosh.

556
00:23:49,884 --> 00:23:51,184
She said, "Oh, my gosh."

557
00:23:55,456 --> 00:23:56,623
- Hi.
- Hello!

558
00:23:56,624 --> 00:23:58,491
(Match pairing: Yu Jin and Yun So)

559
00:23:58,726 --> 00:24:00,727
I said that going on a date
with you would be a total disaster.

560
00:24:00,828 --> 00:24:02,729
- Why?
- I haven't really talked to you much,

561
00:24:03,364 --> 00:24:06,132
- so I thought it'd feel awkward.
- I don't think it'll be awkward with you.

562
00:24:06,133 --> 00:24:07,100
- Really?
- Yes.

563
00:24:07,101 --> 00:24:08,068
Do you know why?

564
00:24:08,169 --> 00:24:11,972
Everyone already thinks
Yun So belongs to Ju Hee.

565
00:24:11,973 --> 00:24:14,674
So going on a date with him feels
like going out with a friend's boyfriend.

566
00:24:14,675 --> 00:24:16,542
That's why she's saying,
"Please don't come to me."

567
00:24:16,543 --> 00:24:20,614
Yun So has already positioned
himself like that.

568
00:24:20,615 --> 00:24:22,516
But this could also be an opportunity.

569
00:24:22,517 --> 00:24:23,517
When they're alone,

570
00:24:24,051 --> 00:24:25,785
he could say, "Actually, that's not true,"

571
00:24:25,786 --> 00:24:28,021
"and I'm really happy
to be here with you now."

572
00:24:28,022 --> 00:24:29,389
- Is that not good?
- Will he?

573
00:24:29,390 --> 00:24:31,424
I don't know.

574
00:24:31,626 --> 00:24:34,061
But no one knows how it'll end.

575
00:24:35,696 --> 00:24:39,432
(The third younger man, Jun Han)

576
00:24:40,435 --> 00:24:42,469
The switcher or the tough guy?
Which one is it?

577
00:24:42,470 --> 00:24:44,705
(Reveal your identity!)

578
00:24:45,306 --> 00:24:47,407
(Jun Han is hurrying toward his woman.)

579
00:24:48,643 --> 00:24:51,445
(Is it Ji Hye, who picked him
because of the switcher card?)

580
00:24:51,946 --> 00:24:55,015
(Or Ju Hee, who had
an overnight date with him?)

581
00:24:55,683 --> 00:24:56,950
(Who picked Jun Han's Charm Card?)

582
00:24:56,951 --> 00:24:59,352
(Ju Hee, Ji Hye)

583
00:24:59,754 --> 00:25:01,722
(Nervous)

584
00:25:01,723 --> 00:25:04,124
Please go to Ji Hye.

585
00:25:04,125 --> 00:25:05,125
(Opening the door)

586
00:25:07,261 --> 00:25:08,161
Hi.

587
00:25:10,665 --> 00:25:11,498
Hi.

588
00:25:14,035 --> 00:25:15,902
(Oh, my gosh.)

589
00:25:15,903 --> 00:25:17,336
What on earth is going on here?

590
00:25:17,672 --> 00:25:19,573
No drama in this world could ever be
as crazy as this.

591
00:25:20,041 --> 00:25:20,907
Hi.

592
00:25:23,744 --> 00:25:26,279
(Disappointed)

593
00:25:26,848 --> 00:25:28,916
- Isn't that Ju Hee's car?
- Right.

594
00:25:29,217 --> 00:25:30,050
Does that bother you?

595
00:25:32,487 --> 00:25:34,221
Why would I be bothered?

596
00:25:35,857 --> 00:25:39,526
I thought it was literally destiny.

597
00:25:40,361 --> 00:25:42,395
I just wanted to hop in a white car.

598
00:25:42,396 --> 00:25:44,297
(He can't help but feel conflicted.)

599
00:25:44,899 --> 00:25:46,233
(Happy)

600
00:25:46,367 --> 00:25:47,300
Are you the touch guy?

601
00:25:47,568 --> 00:25:49,002
- Yes.
- Are you?

602
00:25:49,504 --> 00:25:52,339
My concept today is a tough guy.

603
00:25:52,773 --> 00:25:53,639
A tough guy from Busan.

604
00:25:54,308 --> 00:25:55,141
I'll take care of everything.

605
00:25:55,676 --> 00:25:58,778
(Wincing)

606
00:25:59,247 --> 00:26:00,714
The moment I met Ju Hee,

607
00:26:01,082 --> 00:26:02,249
I felt great.

608
00:26:02,950 --> 00:26:03,985
Our date has come true...

609
00:26:04,853 --> 00:26:06,920
- earlier than I expected.
- True.

610
00:26:07,922 --> 00:26:11,091
(The fourth younger man, Jung Won)

611
00:26:15,463 --> 00:26:17,465
(The only remaining women are
Jin Young...)

612
00:26:17,466 --> 00:26:19,833
(and Ji Hye.)

613
00:26:19,834 --> 00:26:21,134
(Ji Hye, Jin Young)

614
00:26:21,135 --> 00:26:24,805
(Who will he go on a date with?)

615
00:26:25,907 --> 00:26:29,576
(The woman who picked
Jung Won's Charm Card is...)

616
00:26:29,577 --> 00:26:30,477
(Jin Young.)

617
00:26:30,478 --> 00:26:31,711
- What?
- What?

618
00:26:31,879 --> 00:26:33,546
Maybe you got the wrong car.

619
00:26:34,983 --> 00:26:36,983
(Jin Young was waiting for him, actually.)

620
00:26:36,984 --> 00:26:38,752
- I know where I am.
- Seriously?

621
00:26:39,654 --> 00:26:40,487
What?

622
00:26:40,922 --> 00:26:43,423
I didn't imagine this.

623
00:26:44,125 --> 00:26:46,793
It was about each other's charms,

624
00:26:47,028 --> 00:26:49,663
and I never thought she'd pick me...

625
00:26:49,664 --> 00:26:50,931
at all.

626
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:56,736
(Jung Won had promised a date
with Jin Young on the first day.)

627
00:26:56,737 --> 00:27:00,441
- Of course, we should
- We Should?

628
00:27:00,442 --> 00:27:03,009
I really wanted to talk with her today,
no matter what.

629
00:27:03,311 --> 00:27:05,012
And I felt, "Okay, this is it."

630
00:27:05,013 --> 00:27:06,446
Really?

631
00:27:06,714 --> 00:27:09,315
I'm really getting goosebumps.

632
00:27:09,584 --> 00:27:11,952
I didn't even see it in my dreams.

633
00:27:12,186 --> 00:27:15,121
I couldn't believe it so much
that I thought it was rigged.

634
00:27:15,656 --> 00:27:16,990
He came up...

635
00:27:19,026 --> 00:27:20,326
She looks so happy.

636
00:27:20,327 --> 00:27:22,028
I really...

637
00:27:22,797 --> 00:27:25,132
- Those two really match well.
- Definitely.

638
00:27:26,367 --> 00:27:28,802
(Bothered)

639
00:27:29,837 --> 00:27:32,238
(The last younger man, Si Won)

640
00:27:32,374 --> 00:27:33,506
Wait.

641
00:27:34,108 --> 00:27:36,042
The switcher card was Si Won's?

642
00:27:36,411 --> 00:27:37,944
What?

643
00:27:38,879 --> 00:27:40,980
- What a shock.
- Gosh.

644
00:27:40,981 --> 00:27:42,748
Maybe he doesn't even know what it means.

645
00:27:43,184 --> 00:27:44,852
(Cracking up)

646
00:27:44,853 --> 00:27:46,253
So, he doesn't know the meaning?

647
00:27:46,254 --> 00:27:48,155
He might've thought
it was some kind of proverb.

648
00:27:49,857 --> 00:27:52,192
(The owner of the switcher card)

649
00:27:52,493 --> 00:27:53,626
(Smiling)

650
00:27:56,797 --> 00:27:58,264
- Take the passenger seat.
- Gosh.

651
00:27:58,599 --> 00:27:59,532
Why did he go there?

652
00:28:00,134 --> 00:28:01,935
(Finding him cute)

653
00:28:01,936 --> 00:28:04,137
Why did he go to the driver's seat?

654
00:28:04,805 --> 00:28:06,105
He's so clumsy.

655
00:28:07,108 --> 00:28:10,777
(The clumsy boy is
the owner of the switcher card.)

656
00:28:11,712 --> 00:28:12,945
Welcome.

657
00:28:12,946 --> 00:28:14,348
Hi.

658
00:28:15,182 --> 00:28:17,250
- This is interesting.
- Yes.

659
00:28:17,385 --> 00:28:19,654
We said we should go on a date,

660
00:28:19,655 --> 00:28:20,587
- Right.
- and we are now.

661
00:28:21,356 --> 00:28:25,325
Ji Hye was into Si Won's physique
back then.

662
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:27,594
Si Won, let's go on a date sometime.

663
00:28:27,962 --> 00:28:30,965
(Ji Hye's sudden date invitation)

664
00:28:30,966 --> 00:28:31,998
Why are you not answering?

665
00:28:32,967 --> 00:28:34,167
- He did.
- Sounds good.

666
00:28:34,168 --> 00:28:35,135
You did!

667
00:28:36,737 --> 00:28:37,671
And I picked it!

668
00:28:37,672 --> 00:28:39,172
Right. How amazing.

669
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:43,343
The card had a very simple message,
so I picked it.

670
00:28:44,078 --> 00:28:46,479
I just thought that this person must be
very simple.

671
00:28:47,415 --> 00:28:49,316
It said, "The switcher?"

672
00:28:50,284 --> 00:28:51,517
I thought, "The switch could be
off all day long."

673
00:28:52,853 --> 00:28:54,153
(Maybe they both secretly wanted a date.)

674
00:28:54,154 --> 00:28:55,021
You'll see.

675
00:28:56,424 --> 00:28:59,626
(Charm Card Date matching complete)

676
00:28:59,627 --> 00:29:01,128
Aren't Ji Seung and Jin Woo
on their first date,

677
00:29:01,896 --> 00:29:04,297
and Yun So and Yu Jin too?

678
00:29:04,298 --> 00:29:05,599
That's right.

679
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:08,802
There are still pairings
that haven't had a date yet.

680
00:29:09,513 --> 00:29:16,586
(Random dates begin with new excitement.)

681
00:29:17,445 --> 00:29:20,013
(But then, a moment later)

682
00:29:22,172 --> 00:29:23,256
(Would you like to extend the date,)

683
00:29:23,257 --> 00:29:26,486
I can't believe
there's already a choice like this.

684
00:29:26,487 --> 00:29:27,316
(or switch to another man?)

685
00:29:27,355 --> 00:29:32,259
(A shocking message arrived
only for the women.)

686
00:29:32,860 --> 00:29:34,294
Oh, no!

687
00:29:40,201 --> 00:29:44,304
(The results shock everyone.)

688
00:29:45,906 --> 00:29:48,074
Are you kidding me?

689
00:29:49,210 --> 00:29:50,777
It was very annoying.

690
00:29:51,045 --> 00:29:56,116
(Can these dates all continue to the end?)

691
00:29:56,117 --> 00:29:57,951
(Charm Card Date: Jun Han and Ju Hee)

692
00:29:58,052 --> 00:29:58,985
Did you think it was me?

693
00:29:59,253 --> 00:30:01,220
- No, I had no idea.
- No?

694
00:30:02,289 --> 00:30:04,257
Yesterday we all moved together,

695
00:30:05,426 --> 00:30:07,561
but today,
it's just the two of us like this.

696
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,526
It does feel different.

697
00:30:10,193 --> 00:30:12,093
Yesterday felt more like a group outing.

698
00:30:12,093 --> 00:30:15,093
But today really feels like a date.

699
00:30:16,893 --> 00:30:19,160
- You know...
- Oh, my.

700
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:21,493
If I had to describe...

701
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,360
how this date feels...

702
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:28,060
It feels like we've been dating
for months.

703
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:29,760
Is it just me?

704
00:30:29,760 --> 00:30:31,426
Jun Han is really trying his best.

705
00:30:31,426 --> 00:30:32,893
Have I been too casual with you?

706
00:30:32,893 --> 00:30:34,193
I like it when things are casual.

707
00:30:34,193 --> 00:30:35,060
I like keeping things casual too,

708
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:37,260
but then I might start teasing you.

709
00:30:38,760 --> 00:30:40,160
Don't tease me too much.

710
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:44,726
- Does it make you uncomfortable?
- I'm not very comfortable with that.

711
00:30:44,726 --> 00:30:45,960
- You feel pressure?
- Yes.

712
00:30:47,726 --> 00:30:48,526
You don't have to.

713
00:30:48,826 --> 00:30:51,893
(They arrive at the date...)

714
00:30:51,893 --> 00:30:54,326
(with their hearts moving
at different speeds.)

715
00:30:54,326 --> 00:30:55,593
My goodness.

716
00:30:56,526 --> 00:30:57,360
You're glowing.

717
00:30:57,926 --> 00:30:58,893
Turn off your halo.

718
00:30:59,593 --> 00:31:00,893
- Sorry?
- Turn off your halo.

719
00:31:01,226 --> 00:31:02,393
She's not buying it.

720
00:31:02,393 --> 00:31:03,360
How was that?

721
00:31:03,993 --> 00:31:04,960
Was it flattering?

722
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:05,893
I'm not sure.

723
00:31:07,026 --> 00:31:09,093
Come on. Can you at least smile for me?

724
00:31:09,593 --> 00:31:10,360
Please.

725
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:11,360
(Shaking her head)

726
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:13,993
You need to warm her up
before saying things like that.

727
00:31:13,993 --> 00:31:15,426
She's not feeling it at all, is she?

728
00:31:16,193 --> 00:31:18,093
- We're here.
- We're here.

729
00:31:18,393 --> 00:31:20,393
(What will they do on their date?)

730
00:31:20,393 --> 00:31:21,460
- What's this place?
- Are they drawing?

731
00:31:22,493 --> 00:31:25,460
(A keyring-making date...)

732
00:31:25,460 --> 00:31:28,326
(where they draw each other's faces.)

733
00:31:30,193 --> 00:31:32,226
Doing this makes me feel
like we're actually dating.

734
00:31:32,993 --> 00:31:34,160
(Smiling ear to ear)

735
00:31:34,626 --> 00:31:36,060
- Make me look good.
- Okay.

736
00:31:36,993 --> 00:31:37,926
I'll do my best.

737
00:31:39,860 --> 00:31:44,426
(The two draw each other's portraits.)

738
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:46,626
(Peeking)

739
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:49,726
(Staring)

740
00:31:51,126 --> 00:31:54,293
Sneaking a peek at you makes me happy.

741
00:31:55,026 --> 00:31:56,893
(That's absurd.)

742
00:31:57,893 --> 00:31:58,893
Want me to add some shading?

743
00:32:00,226 --> 00:32:01,093
Are you okay with that?

744
00:32:02,693 --> 00:32:03,526
All right.

745
00:32:06,126 --> 00:32:08,193
Your jawline isn't this sharp.

746
00:32:08,193 --> 00:32:10,260
No, I mean... It's not this round.

747
00:32:10,993 --> 00:32:11,926
I'll sharpen it up a little.

748
00:32:11,926 --> 00:32:12,893
You sure talk a lot.

749
00:32:15,226 --> 00:32:16,826
Gosh. I think I'm pretty good at this.

750
00:32:16,826 --> 00:32:17,893
It's really good.

751
00:32:19,060 --> 00:32:20,293
Are you drawing with your mouth?

752
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:24,993
(Even in the same room,
they're worlds apart.)

753
00:32:26,893 --> 00:32:28,226
I think I messed up.

754
00:32:28,226 --> 00:32:29,293
This is a little...

755
00:32:29,293 --> 00:32:31,726
(Despite Ju Hee's lukewarm reaction,
Jun Han is all smiles.)

756
00:32:31,726 --> 00:32:33,726
Maybe that's why she told us
to sketch it in pencil first.

757
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:35,860
My heart was racing.

758
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:38,860
I was over the moon.

759
00:32:40,060 --> 00:32:42,193
Every moment I spent
with her made me happy.

760
00:32:42,593 --> 00:32:43,493
Oh, no.

761
00:32:43,493 --> 00:32:48,226
It really felt like I was dating Ju Hee.

762
00:32:49,526 --> 00:32:53,093
Jun Han is so simple and clear.

763
00:32:53,093 --> 00:32:54,293
We can see through him.

764
00:32:56,360 --> 00:32:57,560
What do you think of this message?

765
00:32:58,026 --> 00:32:59,126
(The keyring Jun Han made)

766
00:32:59,126 --> 00:33:01,326
That's a nice drawing.

767
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:02,560
It's cute.

768
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:06,460
(He's just happy.)

769
00:33:08,260 --> 00:33:09,060
You too.

770
00:33:10,660 --> 00:33:12,126
Gosh. She's really good.
It looks exactly like him.

771
00:33:12,860 --> 00:33:14,260
Don't throw it away, okay?

772
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:16,626
Don't lose it.

773
00:33:16,626 --> 00:33:17,726
I won't throw it away.

774
00:33:17,726 --> 00:33:20,593
No matter what he does,
Ju Hee stays indifferent.

775
00:33:21,860 --> 00:33:23,226
- Let's go.
- We're done.

776
00:33:23,226 --> 00:33:24,126
It was fun.

777
00:33:24,126 --> 00:33:25,926
(Will Jun Han's sincerity reach Ju Hee?)

778
00:33:25,926 --> 00:33:28,393
Here's how Jun Han sees it.

779
00:33:28,393 --> 00:33:30,860
"She used her Staying Night Together
Date Ticket on me."

780
00:33:30,860 --> 00:33:33,493
"That means she must really like me!"

781
00:33:33,493 --> 00:33:34,326
Right.

782
00:33:34,326 --> 00:33:37,493
"If that's the case,
then I'm all in on her too!"

783
00:33:37,493 --> 00:33:40,893
Thinking that way probably makes it
easier for him to overlook...

784
00:33:40,893 --> 00:33:41,893
her lukewarm reactions.

785
00:33:41,893 --> 00:33:44,026
He might think she's just acting reserved
because she already showed...

786
00:33:44,026 --> 00:33:46,993
how interested she was
by using her Ticket on him.

787
00:33:47,285 --> 00:33:48,118
Let's go.

788
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:50,126
I'll get you there safely.

789
00:33:50,126 --> 00:33:51,626
Thank you.

790
00:33:51,626 --> 00:33:53,926
This date is going to be lively, isn't it?

791
00:33:53,926 --> 00:33:55,726
I'm curious to see how it goes.

792
00:33:55,726 --> 00:33:57,760
You... Oh, right.

793
00:33:57,760 --> 00:34:00,693
You would've preferred
to be matched with Ju Hee, right?

794
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:02,093
- For today's date?
- Yes.

795
00:34:02,593 --> 00:34:03,726
This Random Date.

796
00:34:04,526 --> 00:34:05,326
Yes.

797
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,760
- Honestly, yes.
- All right.

798
00:34:08,393 --> 00:34:11,826
But what did you think
when you found out it was me?

799
00:34:11,826 --> 00:34:12,660
- You?
- Yes.

800
00:34:12,926 --> 00:34:14,960
I had no idea who I'd be matched with.

801
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:16,526
Then I opened it, and it was you.

802
00:34:16,526 --> 00:34:20,026
So I thought we'd probably have
a fun conversation.

803
00:34:20,026 --> 00:34:20,960
Not a heart-fluttering one?

804
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:23,726
- Just a fun one?
- That's not what I meant.

805
00:34:23,726 --> 00:34:24,793
I never said that.

806
00:34:24,793 --> 00:34:27,493
"So today's just not my day."

807
00:34:27,493 --> 00:34:30,793
- "I'll just have fun."
- That's not what I meant.

808
00:34:30,793 --> 00:34:34,593
I've always thought you and I would click.

809
00:34:34,593 --> 00:34:36,260
So I figured today would be fun.

810
00:34:36,260 --> 00:34:37,860
Okay. I get it.

811
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:39,493
You're pouting.

812
00:34:39,793 --> 00:34:43,526
- You were like, "Oh... okay."
- No, I wasn't.

813
00:34:43,526 --> 00:34:46,460
(Yu Jin's playful teasing lightens
the mood.)

814
00:34:46,460 --> 00:34:47,860
Okay. Now you're drinking.

815
00:34:48,260 --> 00:34:49,393
You must've been thirsty.

816
00:34:52,793 --> 00:34:53,726
See? We really click.

817
00:34:53,726 --> 00:34:55,293
This is how a conversation should flow.

818
00:34:56,126 --> 00:34:58,726
Yun So seems comfortable...

819
00:34:58,726 --> 00:35:01,893
around everyone except Ju Hee.

820
00:35:01,893 --> 00:35:03,226
- His tone is completely different.
- Exactly.

821
00:35:04,093 --> 00:35:05,660
Have you ever dated an older woman?

822
00:35:05,660 --> 00:35:07,726
I've never dated an older woman.

823
00:35:08,493 --> 00:35:09,626
I always thought...

824
00:35:10,526 --> 00:35:13,893
I'd be the one taking the lead
in a relationship.

825
00:35:14,560 --> 00:35:18,293
But here, I actually want someone else
to take the lead.

826
00:35:18,293 --> 00:35:19,126
Really?

827
00:35:19,126 --> 00:35:21,826
- I kind of want to follow.
- Really?

828
00:35:22,326 --> 00:35:24,026
Want me to lead you around?

829
00:35:24,026 --> 00:35:26,260
So today... Do you want to lead or follow?

830
00:35:26,593 --> 00:35:27,393
- Today?
- Yes.

831
00:35:27,393 --> 00:35:28,626
I want to follow.

832
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:29,626
Okay.

833
00:35:31,095 --> 00:35:32,793
- Then I'd like you to lead me.
- Deal.

834
00:35:32,793 --> 00:35:33,960
- Let's go.
- Okay.

835
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:35,726
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

836
00:35:36,393 --> 00:35:37,593
(Aren't they too cute together?)

837
00:35:37,593 --> 00:35:38,793
She's taking the lead today?

838
00:35:38,793 --> 00:35:40,060
This is so much fun.

839
00:35:40,060 --> 00:35:41,360
- I love it.
- Me too.

840
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,226
I love their vibe.

841
00:35:42,660 --> 00:35:45,493
- I love it.
- Will you be my lady today?

842
00:35:45,493 --> 00:35:46,560
Okay.

843
00:35:48,326 --> 00:35:50,526
(Shy)

844
00:35:51,426 --> 00:35:52,526
(Lost in conversation, they reach
their destination before they know it.)

845
00:35:52,526 --> 00:35:54,293
- We're here already?
- We're almost there.

846
00:35:54,293 --> 00:35:55,660
- What happened?
- Time flew by.

847
00:35:55,660 --> 00:35:58,026
Time really flies when I'm talking to you.

848
00:36:05,826 --> 00:36:08,726
Do you like the mountains
or the ocean more?

849
00:36:09,126 --> 00:36:11,126
I used to love the ocean.

850
00:36:11,493 --> 00:36:15,660
Back when I was young enough to swim.

851
00:36:16,393 --> 00:36:17,793
(Hesitating)

852
00:36:17,793 --> 00:36:20,460
Now I feel too old for that.

853
00:36:20,460 --> 00:36:21,393
Too old?

854
00:36:21,860 --> 00:36:24,260
You're talking about age in front of me?

855
00:36:24,793 --> 00:36:26,160
There's something on your shirt.

856
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:28,260
- You always have something on you.
- I know, right?

857
00:36:28,260 --> 00:36:29,093
- Here.
- Let me get it.

858
00:36:29,093 --> 00:36:31,726
(The drive brings
the two noticeably closer.)

859
00:36:31,726 --> 00:36:33,626
Could these two actually hit it off?

860
00:36:33,626 --> 00:36:35,426
You know...

861
00:36:35,426 --> 00:36:36,993
This is even better than I expected.

862
00:36:37,493 --> 00:36:39,660
I hope it turns out like those dramas...

863
00:36:40,093 --> 00:36:41,760
Where they start off
feeling like siblings,

864
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:42,960
but end up becoming a couple.

865
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:43,960
I know.

866
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:47,526
(Excuse me.)

867
00:36:47,993 --> 00:36:49,626
I'm the leader today.

868
00:36:51,126 --> 00:36:52,426
(Protecting)

869
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:55,726
So cool. You're really good at this.

870
00:36:55,726 --> 00:36:57,393
- I love it.
- Not bad, right?

871
00:36:57,993 --> 00:37:01,260
This beautiful weather makes me so happy.

872
00:37:01,260 --> 00:37:02,160
- I know.
- Right?

873
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:04,693
- I'm so glad.
- I love it.

874
00:37:04,693 --> 00:37:06,126
(Even the weather helps their first date.)

875
00:37:06,726 --> 00:37:08,460
Wait. Here.

876
00:37:09,693 --> 00:37:10,593
I'll help you.

877
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:11,960
There you go.

878
00:37:12,593 --> 00:37:13,460
Thank you.

879
00:37:13,460 --> 00:37:14,760
(Escorted by Yu Jin,
he heads onto the Skywalk.)

880
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:15,760
I want to dive right in.

881
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:16,693
It looks so refreshing.

882
00:37:17,126 --> 00:37:18,293
You love swimming.

883
00:37:18,693 --> 00:37:20,026
I love it up here.

884
00:37:21,226 --> 00:37:23,093
The sunshine is beautiful today.

885
00:37:23,093 --> 00:37:25,226
The weather is perfect.

886
00:37:25,526 --> 00:37:27,526
I love all the different views
from up here.

887
00:37:27,526 --> 00:37:29,960
- You can even see the cherry blossoms.
- The cherry blossoms...

888
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,593
- The Cherry blossoms.
- And the mountains.

889
00:37:33,126 --> 00:37:34,360
We have to take a picture here.

890
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:36,093
I'll take one for you.

891
00:37:36,093 --> 00:37:38,093
- Please make it a good one.
- Here. I'll take your bag.

892
00:37:38,326 --> 00:37:39,593
Want me to pose?

893
00:37:40,593 --> 00:37:42,726
- Give me your best pose.
- I'll take a great shot.

894
00:37:43,726 --> 00:37:45,626
Hold on. I can't see clearly.

895
00:37:46,593 --> 00:37:49,226
In 1, 2, 3.

896
00:37:49,993 --> 00:37:53,326
- Gosh. You're such a good model.
- Really?

897
00:37:53,326 --> 00:37:54,126
Yes.

898
00:37:55,926 --> 00:37:57,726
(Sticking closer)

899
00:37:57,926 --> 00:37:59,160
- That's a great shot.
- It's a work of art.

900
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:00,026
I love it.

901
00:38:00,260 --> 00:38:01,093
Now, together.

902
00:38:01,660 --> 00:38:02,526
I'll stand in front.

903
00:38:03,693 --> 00:38:04,893
In 1, 2, 3.

904
00:38:05,560 --> 00:38:07,393
Since I'm taller...

905
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:09,526
They've definitely got chemistry,
don't they?

906
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:13,493
It feels like I'm taking a selfie
with a celebrity.

907
00:38:13,493 --> 00:38:14,660
That's exactly how I felt.

908
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:15,493
"Can I get a selfie with you?"

909
00:38:16,626 --> 00:38:19,160
- Taking pictures is so much fun.
- It really is.

910
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:21,293
- It's so interesting.
- Isn't it?

911
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:24,193
I really don't like
having my picture taken.

912
00:38:24,193 --> 00:38:28,293
I actually modeled a long time ago.

913
00:38:28,293 --> 00:38:29,460
- But...
- No wonder.

914
00:38:29,460 --> 00:38:30,593
- Really?
- Yes.

915
00:38:30,593 --> 00:38:32,726
But the moment
a photo shoot was scheduled,

916
00:38:32,726 --> 00:38:35,060
I'd start getting really stressed out.

917
00:38:35,060 --> 00:38:36,126
- Really?
- Yes.

918
00:38:36,126 --> 00:38:37,860
That must've been exhausting.

919
00:38:37,860 --> 00:38:39,093
That's why I quit.

920
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:44,393
That's such a shame.
You have such a beautiful face...

921
00:38:44,393 --> 00:38:46,260
- and an amazing figure.
- Keep going.

922
00:38:47,193 --> 00:38:49,126
If you'd stayed in modeling...

923
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:51,993
I don't think you'd be here with me.
You'd probably be...

924
00:38:53,026 --> 00:38:54,026
as famous as Han Hye Jin?

925
00:38:56,426 --> 00:38:57,360
Han Hye Jin?

926
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:59,793
You tilted your head so much just now.

927
00:38:59,793 --> 00:39:01,526
Yun So's in trouble.

928
00:39:01,526 --> 00:39:03,193
(No way.)

929
00:39:04,326 --> 00:39:05,493
Stop it.

930
00:39:06,393 --> 00:39:09,526
- You told me to keep going.
- Not that far.

931
00:39:10,126 --> 00:39:11,760
(Their banter comes naturally.)

932
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:13,426
The two have great chemistry.

933
00:39:13,426 --> 00:39:15,660
- Seriously.
- It's like watching a romantic comedy.

934
00:39:15,660 --> 00:39:18,564
I got to see
a completely different side of Yun So.

935
00:39:18,565 --> 00:39:20,358
- That's good.
- It worked.

936
00:39:20,460 --> 00:39:23,726
Taking pictures with him made me
remember not just the scenery,

937
00:39:23,726 --> 00:39:27,726
but also the atmosphere
and the feelings we shared.

938
00:39:27,726 --> 00:39:30,393
That really stayed with me.

939
00:39:31,026 --> 00:39:32,926
She quit modeling...

940
00:39:32,926 --> 00:39:34,893
because she hated
having her picture taken,

941
00:39:34,893 --> 00:39:37,693
- yet she loved every photo...
- She loves it.

942
00:39:37,693 --> 00:39:38,493
she took with him.

943
00:39:38,493 --> 00:39:40,560
She said she was having fun.

944
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:42,393
- That's a really positive sign for me.
- Yes.

945
00:39:43,493 --> 00:39:44,426
(Charm Card Date: Jin Woo and Ji Seung)

946
00:39:44,426 --> 00:39:45,493
I can't wait.

947
00:39:45,493 --> 00:39:47,326
What an unexpected pairing.

948
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:50,660
I'll get you there safely today.

949
00:39:51,326 --> 00:39:54,193
Do women talk to each other a lot?

950
00:39:54,193 --> 00:39:55,993
Do you talk about the men too?

951
00:39:56,293 --> 00:40:00,093
I'm not really the type
to share my feelings.

952
00:40:00,526 --> 00:40:02,393
But I listen.

953
00:40:02,393 --> 00:40:03,793
Sometimes I share mine too.

954
00:40:05,225 --> 00:40:07,593
What do you think about me?

955
00:40:07,954 --> 00:40:11,957
Overall, I feel like
you're not really letting...

956
00:40:12,532 --> 00:40:15,567
the guys get close to you.

957
00:40:16,269 --> 00:40:17,836
Right. I'm not.

958
00:40:18,839 --> 00:40:20,739
I tend to take my time.

959
00:40:21,408 --> 00:40:23,709
I tend to take a long time.

960
00:40:24,778 --> 00:40:28,442
After learning about each other's jobs,

961
00:40:29,479 --> 00:40:31,918
I personally felt close to you...

962
00:40:31,919 --> 00:40:33,619
even though we didn't really have
a connection.

963
00:40:33,620 --> 00:40:34,554
Why?

964
00:40:34,821 --> 00:40:35,754
(When revealing their jobs)

965
00:40:35,755 --> 00:40:37,489
I used to interpret too.

966
00:40:37,758 --> 00:40:39,525
- Really?
- I was an interpreter...

967
00:40:39,860 --> 00:40:41,527
- for foreign models at a modeling agency.
- Is that so?

968
00:40:42,095 --> 00:40:46,298
(They found out
they both have worked as interpreters.)

969
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,735
Actually, I also thought...

970
00:40:48,935 --> 00:40:51,303
that was something unexpected about you.

971
00:40:51,304 --> 00:40:54,174
I enjoyed interpreting
more than any other job I've had.

972
00:40:54,175 --> 00:40:56,642
- That's cool.
- That's an unexpected charm.

973
00:40:56,643 --> 00:40:57,509
Really?

974
00:40:58,078 --> 00:40:59,578
Yesterday,

975
00:40:59,713 --> 00:41:01,681
you had your top two sit next to you.

976
00:41:02,516 --> 00:41:04,784
I felt like...

977
00:41:05,485 --> 00:41:08,387
you never really treated me
like you were into me,

978
00:41:09,089 --> 00:41:11,791
so I thought being your second choice
didn't mean much.

979
00:41:12,459 --> 00:41:13,325
You're right.

980
00:41:13,894 --> 00:41:15,895
But there's a story behind it.

981
00:41:16,196 --> 00:41:19,398
When you talked about your dating style,
I felt like it was similar to mine.

982
00:41:19,933 --> 00:41:22,001
You were talking about how you see things,

983
00:41:22,002 --> 00:41:24,503
- and how you put love first.
- Yes.

984
00:41:24,504 --> 00:41:26,005
That got me curious.

985
00:41:26,006 --> 00:41:28,207
- When I said I put love before work?
- Yes.

986
00:41:28,208 --> 00:41:29,942
"We're working to live."

987
00:41:29,943 --> 00:41:32,478
- "We're not living to work."
- Exactly.

988
00:41:32,779 --> 00:41:33,846
To me, it's important...

989
00:41:34,647 --> 00:41:38,083
to have fun with my partner
even when we're doing nothing.

990
00:41:38,084 --> 00:41:38,917
I agree.

991
00:41:39,853 --> 00:41:42,955
I like dating someone
who lives close to me.

992
00:41:44,057 --> 00:41:46,859
You have your favorite spots
in your neighborhood.

993
00:41:46,860 --> 00:41:48,060
Right.

994
00:41:48,462 --> 00:41:50,296
You can just get ice cream
and go for a walk together.

995
00:41:50,297 --> 00:41:52,064
(Surprised)

996
00:41:52,065 --> 00:41:54,200
You sound just like me.

997
00:41:55,669 --> 00:41:57,937
(When asked what kind of date she prefers)

998
00:41:57,938 --> 00:42:00,706
Just eat ice cream while taking a walk.

999
00:42:01,675 --> 00:42:04,410
I just want to have a good time
with him...

1000
00:42:04,411 --> 00:42:06,846
even if there's nothing special.

1001
00:42:08,348 --> 00:42:09,214
(His answer is exactly the same.)

1002
00:42:09,215 --> 00:42:10,015
That's fascinating.

1003
00:42:10,317 --> 00:42:12,351
I said exactly the same thing.

1004
00:42:13,553 --> 00:42:14,553
That's so interesting.

1005
00:42:14,554 --> 00:42:15,821
They have things in common.

1006
00:42:15,822 --> 00:42:17,689
You just walk together,

1007
00:42:17,690 --> 00:42:18,891
sharing earphones.

1008
00:42:18,892 --> 00:42:20,025
I like doing things like that.

1009
00:42:20,026 --> 00:42:22,694
But you feel like you have a lot
in common,

1010
00:42:22,695 --> 00:42:23,795
you move forward fast at the start.

1011
00:42:23,796 --> 00:42:25,631
- Right. You feel attracted to each other.
- It makes you comfortable.

1012
00:42:26,533 --> 00:42:28,000
Looks like we'll take a cable car.

1013
00:42:28,025 --> 00:42:29,092
(The two arrive at their date spot.)

1014
00:42:29,135 --> 00:42:30,902
I think
I've never taken a cable car before.

1015
00:42:30,903 --> 00:42:33,238
(The cable car will make them
have a special time in the air.)

1016
00:42:33,239 --> 00:42:34,206
It looks so nice.

1017
00:42:34,508 --> 00:42:36,042
I've always wanted to do this.

1018
00:42:36,943 --> 00:42:39,211
(Ji Seung is excited to ride a cable car
for the first time.)

1019
00:42:39,212 --> 00:42:40,512
The weather is so nice.

1020
00:42:41,882 --> 00:42:43,950
Are you dressed up enough
for pictures today?

1021
00:42:44,584 --> 00:42:45,684
- Yes.
- Do you want pictures?

1022
00:42:45,685 --> 00:42:46,552
I'll take the best photos you've ever had.

1023
00:42:46,553 --> 00:42:47,953
- I'm really good at taking pictures.
- Really?

1024
00:42:47,954 --> 00:42:48,854
I'm excited.

1025
00:42:49,556 --> 00:42:50,823
Please go this way.

1026
00:42:50,824 --> 00:42:51,790
Okay.

1027
00:42:51,791 --> 00:42:53,559
Jin Woo is really good...

1028
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:55,561
at making conversation with the girls.

1029
00:42:55,830 --> 00:42:57,163
He's a good person.

1030
00:42:57,164 --> 00:42:59,366
The door will close automatically.
Enjoy your ride.

1031
00:42:59,367 --> 00:43:00,499
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1032
00:43:01,968 --> 00:43:02,968
It's fast.

1033
00:43:05,505 --> 00:43:06,905
(Amazed)

1034
00:43:06,906 --> 00:43:08,640
(Exclaiming)

1035
00:43:09,342 --> 00:43:10,475
(A lake stretching out
in front of their eyes)

1036
00:43:10,476 --> 00:43:11,777
It looks so nice.

1037
00:43:14,848 --> 00:43:17,382
I'm so happy. What do I do?

1038
00:43:17,383 --> 00:43:18,717
Sit here. I'll take your pictures.

1039
00:43:20,020 --> 00:43:20,987
It's nice.

1040
00:43:20,988 --> 00:43:22,755
(Jin Woo even tells her where to sit.)

1041
00:43:23,256 --> 00:43:24,323
What kind of picture do you want?

1042
00:43:24,324 --> 00:43:26,124
Your whole body or your upper body?

1043
00:43:26,125 --> 00:43:27,526
At my knees.

1044
00:43:27,761 --> 00:43:28,894
Show the legs a bit.

1045
00:43:28,895 --> 00:43:29,795
From the legs?

1046
00:43:29,863 --> 00:43:30,830
That's not easy.

1047
00:43:30,831 --> 00:43:32,131
Let me see.

1048
00:43:32,132 --> 00:43:33,399
(Hunching)

1049
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:34,533
He's indeed a younger man.

1050
00:43:35,468 --> 00:43:36,501
That's cute.

1051
00:43:37,070 --> 00:43:37,936
He's adorable.

1052
00:43:39,324 --> 00:43:40,205
In 1, 2, 3.

1053
00:43:40,206 --> 00:43:41,206
(Hunching to take good pictures of her)

1054
00:43:41,841 --> 00:43:42,774
(The two look good
with the lake behind them.)

1055
00:43:42,775 --> 00:43:44,643
I feel like he has an older sister.

1056
00:43:45,211 --> 00:43:46,144
In 1, 2, 3.

1057
00:43:47,514 --> 00:43:48,514
In 1, 2, 3.

1058
00:43:49,382 --> 00:43:51,750
You're doing great. Keep going.
That was so natural.

1059
00:43:51,751 --> 00:43:54,353
(His compliments make her feel good.)

1060
00:43:54,354 --> 00:43:56,955
(Happy)

1061
00:43:58,391 --> 00:43:59,524
He takes good pictures.

1062
00:44:01,328 --> 00:44:04,730
You took good pictures. I like this.

1063
00:44:04,731 --> 00:44:06,565
They're good, right? I told you.

1064
00:44:06,566 --> 00:44:08,034
- You're good at this.
- I am!

1065
00:44:08,035 --> 00:44:10,337
I'm the best wife material.
I mean, husband material.

1066
00:44:10,503 --> 00:44:11,369
Wife material.

1067
00:44:11,638 --> 00:44:13,673
- I like the view.
- That's cute.

1068
00:44:13,807 --> 00:44:15,141
Shall we see it together from here?

1069
00:44:15,442 --> 00:44:16,609
This side looks more beautiful.

1070
00:44:17,444 --> 00:44:18,711
- This side is better.
- This view is better.

1071
00:44:18,712 --> 00:44:22,114
(The two seem a lot closer.)

1072
00:44:22,449 --> 00:44:25,284
(Staring)

1073
00:44:26,653 --> 00:44:28,220
When I'm at Yeon House,

1074
00:44:28,989 --> 00:44:30,523
there's so much going on.

1075
00:44:30,524 --> 00:44:32,158
Right. But when you go outside...

1076
00:44:32,159 --> 00:44:33,893
But it's so peaceful now.

1077
00:44:33,894 --> 00:44:34,760
It is.

1078
00:44:37,397 --> 00:44:39,898
If I go on a date with you again,
I should bring a jacket.

1079
00:44:40,500 --> 00:44:41,568
Do I look cold?

1080
00:44:41,569 --> 00:44:43,435
You always wear short bottoms.

1081
00:44:43,937 --> 00:44:46,105
He's thoughtful.

1082
00:44:46,106 --> 00:44:47,406
(That's cute.)

1083
00:44:47,575 --> 00:44:49,442
Who did you...

1084
00:44:50,176 --> 00:44:52,911
Who did you hope to see?

1085
00:44:53,146 --> 00:44:55,715
You were expecting someone, right?

1086
00:44:55,716 --> 00:44:56,782
Ji Hye?

1087
00:44:57,250 --> 00:44:58,483
- Today's date?
- Yes.

1088
00:44:58,484 --> 00:45:00,586
When you were writing your Charm Card.

1089
00:45:01,021 --> 00:45:02,855
(Hesitating)

1090
00:45:02,856 --> 00:45:04,691
That didn't make me feel disappointed...

1091
00:45:04,692 --> 00:45:06,959
or stop me from enjoying our date.

1092
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:08,361
I'm...

1093
00:45:08,996 --> 00:45:12,264
spending time with you
as a man and a woman.

1094
00:45:12,265 --> 00:45:14,266
- Right.
- My gosh.

1095
00:45:14,501 --> 00:45:15,835
She liked that answer.

1096
00:45:15,836 --> 00:45:16,936
"Look at this guy."

1097
00:45:16,937 --> 00:45:17,770
"Look at you."

1098
00:45:19,205 --> 00:45:22,741
(Ji Seung and Jin Woo are getting closer.)

1099
00:45:23,176 --> 00:45:25,544
(Charm Card Date, Jung Won and Jin Young)

1100
00:45:25,545 --> 00:45:27,446
I'm curious about these two.

1101
00:45:27,447 --> 00:45:28,414
I wonder how this goes.

1102
00:45:28,982 --> 00:45:30,649
By the way, here's something about me.

1103
00:45:30,950 --> 00:45:32,817
- What?
- This is my first time...

1104
00:45:33,119 --> 00:45:35,120
being a passenger while a woman drives.

1105
00:45:35,121 --> 00:45:36,088
Really?

1106
00:45:36,657 --> 00:45:39,458
There are lots of things
these guys haven't done before.

1107
00:45:40,226 --> 00:45:41,493
How old are they?

1108
00:45:42,328 --> 00:45:45,263
When I was writing my Charm Card,

1109
00:45:46,032 --> 00:45:48,367
I thought I should hide my identity...

1110
00:45:48,368 --> 00:45:50,202
so you guys wouldn't guess who it was.

1111
00:45:50,937 --> 00:45:53,705
You made it hard to guess on purpose.

1112
00:45:53,706 --> 00:45:56,909
No. I'm more serious than you think.

1113
00:45:57,243 --> 00:45:58,811
I couldn't even guess.

1114
00:45:58,812 --> 00:46:00,845
That's why I wanted to go
on a 1-on-1 date with you.

1115
00:46:01,214 --> 00:46:02,514
I'm different...

1116
00:46:03,216 --> 00:46:04,816
when I'm alone,

1117
00:46:04,817 --> 00:46:07,219
with people, or at work.

1118
00:46:07,520 --> 00:46:09,020
Let's get to know each other.

1119
00:46:11,458 --> 00:46:12,291
When I saw that card,

1120
00:46:12,292 --> 00:46:15,428
I was like, "Let me see
how happy you can make me today."

1121
00:46:15,895 --> 00:46:17,128
I feel confident.

1122
00:46:18,565 --> 00:46:19,865
The cherry blossoms look pretty.

1123
00:46:21,268 --> 00:46:22,201
Okay.

1124
00:46:22,202 --> 00:46:23,603
(Arriving at their date spot)

1125
00:46:23,604 --> 00:46:25,004
- It's nice.
- It's close.

1126
00:46:25,305 --> 00:46:26,538
It didn't take long. Nice.

1127
00:46:28,274 --> 00:46:30,175
(A themed date
where you can interact with alpacas)

1128
00:46:30,176 --> 00:46:31,109
Look at the alpacas.

1129
00:46:33,012 --> 00:46:34,446
Oh, my. That's so cute.

1130
00:46:35,248 --> 00:46:38,317
- They're right here.
- They're adorable.

1131
00:46:38,318 --> 00:46:39,184
(Nice to meet you.)

1132
00:46:39,720 --> 00:46:42,988
I want to feed them.

1133
00:46:43,456 --> 00:46:44,256
Me too.

1134
00:46:44,257 --> 00:46:45,957
- You go first.
- Okay.

1135
00:46:45,958 --> 00:46:47,225
"Food for the animals."

1136
00:46:47,761 --> 00:46:48,627
Where is it?

1137
00:46:48,628 --> 00:46:49,895
Wait.

1138
00:46:51,331 --> 00:46:52,564
- One cup.
- It's coming out.

1139
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:54,633
(Excited)

1140
00:46:54,634 --> 00:46:55,467
Awesome.

1141
00:46:56,069 --> 00:46:57,770
Let's go. This is going to be fun.

1142
00:46:58,972 --> 00:46:59,972
(Gasping)

1143
00:47:00,573 --> 00:47:02,741
(It saw the food.)

1144
00:47:03,777 --> 00:47:05,611
It comes as soon as it sees the food.

1145
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:08,213
Wait.

1146
00:47:10,016 --> 00:47:11,350
Gosh. Wait!

1147
00:47:11,584 --> 00:47:15,020
(Taking the entire container)

1148
00:47:15,021 --> 00:47:16,021
That's a gangster!

1149
00:47:16,289 --> 00:47:17,056
(That's so funny.)

1150
00:47:17,081 --> 00:47:18,581
That's an alpha male!

1151
00:47:18,925 --> 00:47:20,192
That's a true alpha male!

1152
00:47:20,395 --> 00:47:23,428
(Self-claimed alpha males,
are you watching this?)

1153
00:47:24,130 --> 00:47:25,197
It's eating well.

1154
00:47:25,198 --> 00:47:26,220
If I try to take it away,

1155
00:47:26,221 --> 00:47:27,467
- it might bite me.
- It might bite you.

1156
00:47:27,468 --> 00:47:28,734
- Take it away.
- Let me take it away.

1157
00:47:29,068 --> 00:47:29,934
Give this.

1158
00:47:30,537 --> 00:47:31,370
Here.

1159
00:47:34,007 --> 00:47:35,541
- It's smart.
- So cute.

1160
00:47:35,542 --> 00:47:36,442
You're smart.

1161
00:47:36,676 --> 00:47:38,342
Who do you want to feed?

1162
00:47:38,343 --> 00:47:40,312
- That kid.
- That kid?

1163
00:47:40,680 --> 00:47:42,714
- Baby. You have some too.
- Hey, baby.

1164
00:47:42,715 --> 00:47:43,448
(Puffy)

1165
00:47:43,449 --> 00:47:46,985
- Their fur is so fluffy.
- Aren't they cute?

1166
00:47:47,854 --> 00:47:48,821
Gosh!

1167
00:47:48,822 --> 00:47:50,189
This one bit me.

1168
00:47:50,190 --> 00:47:51,023
It did?

1169
00:47:51,524 --> 00:47:52,557
- Are you okay?
- I got bitten.

1170
00:47:52,558 --> 00:47:53,558
(Worried)

1171
00:47:55,862 --> 00:47:57,462
Guys, enjoy.

1172
00:47:57,463 --> 00:47:58,497
(Going to another alpaca)

1173
00:47:59,499 --> 00:48:01,433
It scared me.

1174
00:48:02,101 --> 00:48:03,435
- Where?
- Wait.

1175
00:48:03,436 --> 00:48:04,235
Hey.

1176
00:48:04,537 --> 00:48:06,037
Stop.

1177
00:48:06,506 --> 00:48:08,407
(Naturally going behind Jung Won)

1178
00:48:08,408 --> 00:48:09,975
Jung Won doesn't avoid them.

1179
00:48:09,976 --> 00:48:12,688
- Its eyes look weird.
- I got it.

1180
00:48:13,348 --> 00:48:14,313
It's cute.

1181
00:48:14,948 --> 00:48:15,814
Done.

1182
00:48:15,815 --> 00:48:17,349
(Thank you.)

1183
00:48:17,984 --> 00:48:18,784
It's cute.

1184
00:48:19,052 --> 00:48:19,852
Are you happy?

1185
00:48:22,722 --> 00:48:24,823
The alpaca date was so romantic.

1186
00:48:24,824 --> 00:48:26,658
When we were feeding them,

1187
00:48:27,160 --> 00:48:31,063
my heart fluttered
like we were into each other.

1188
00:48:32,166 --> 00:48:33,999
I liked that feeling.

1189
00:48:36,069 --> 00:48:37,903
I really like it here.

1190
00:48:38,705 --> 00:48:39,638
I know.

1191
00:48:40,139 --> 00:48:41,473
This is a cherry blossom path.

1192
00:48:41,474 --> 00:48:44,008
It really feels like a date now, right?

1193
00:48:44,009 --> 00:48:46,277
Yes. It feels like a real date.

1194
00:48:46,278 --> 00:48:47,112
Yes.

1195
00:48:49,249 --> 00:48:50,182
Have a seat.

1196
00:48:50,183 --> 00:48:51,151
(The two are now at a cafe.)

1197
00:48:51,152 --> 00:48:52,418
The view is so nice here.

1198
00:48:58,258 --> 00:49:01,327
So, I'm really curious about this.

1199
00:49:02,328 --> 00:49:05,163
About the Love Room yesterday.

1200
00:49:05,164 --> 00:49:06,031
The Love Room?

1201
00:49:06,032 --> 00:49:07,799
- How much fun did you have...
- Right.

1202
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:08,933
in the Love Room?

1203
00:49:09,135 --> 00:49:10,801
It's been bothering him.

1204
00:49:10,802 --> 00:49:12,437
I've been meaning to ask.

1205
00:49:12,772 --> 00:49:13,772
In the Love Room?

1206
00:49:13,973 --> 00:49:15,907
We had more fun than I thought.

1207
00:49:15,908 --> 00:49:17,642
We just had some wine...

1208
00:49:18,044 --> 00:49:19,945
and swam in the hot tub.

1209
00:49:19,946 --> 00:49:20,946
You guys swam too?

1210
00:49:20,947 --> 00:49:22,647
Well, technically, we didn't,

1211
00:49:22,648 --> 00:49:23,449
but we enjoyed the tub.

1212
00:49:23,450 --> 00:49:25,417
We were in there for a while.

1213
00:49:25,418 --> 00:49:26,852
- Is that so?
- Until like 3 a.m.?

1214
00:49:27,086 --> 00:49:27,852
- Like 3 a.m.?
- Yes.

1215
00:49:28,454 --> 00:49:29,721
- That's a long time.
- Yes.

1216
00:49:29,722 --> 00:49:30,955
With that much detail?

1217
00:49:31,925 --> 00:49:34,059
We had way more to talk
about than I thought.

1218
00:49:35,095 --> 00:49:38,296
What did you talk about with Yun So?

1219
00:49:38,665 --> 00:49:41,499
Yun So and I talked a lot about Ju Hee.

1220
00:49:42,735 --> 00:49:44,069
You talked a lot about the third person.

1221
00:49:44,470 --> 00:49:46,871
Yes. I think so.

1222
00:49:48,541 --> 00:49:51,309
That part bothered me.

1223
00:49:51,744 --> 00:49:54,646
She could've liked him more
after spending the night together.

1224
00:49:55,148 --> 00:49:58,417
But thankfully, it seems like
she's not really interested.

1225
00:49:58,418 --> 00:50:00,986
She didn't talk about him
like she was into him.

1226
00:50:01,223 --> 00:50:02,320
So that was good.

1227
00:50:03,873 --> 00:50:07,026
Then, how did you feel...

1228
00:50:07,460 --> 00:50:12,460
when Ju Hee chose Jun Han
and went on a date with him?

1229
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:17,393
(Jin Young hesitates
when asked about Jun Han.)

1230
00:50:17,969 --> 00:50:21,569
(He's curious about Jin Young's feelings
toward Jun Han.)

1231
00:50:23,126 --> 00:50:25,526
Honestly, it did not feel pleasant.

1232
00:50:25,526 --> 00:50:28,093
I know he has feelings for me.

1233
00:50:28,460 --> 00:50:30,626
But I do not have full confidence in him,

1234
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:32,693
so it feels unfair to expect him
to be the only one fully invested...

1235
00:50:32,693 --> 00:50:37,826
- and only look my way.
- Right.

1236
00:50:37,826 --> 00:50:42,193
Still, when I thought about
him spending the night with another girl,

1237
00:50:43,460 --> 00:50:47,060
I felt a bit complicated.

1238
00:50:51,093 --> 00:50:53,226
When did you feel the most complicated?

1239
00:50:54,193 --> 00:50:55,093
- Me?
- Yes.

1240
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:57,226
I was really confused...

1241
00:50:58,793 --> 00:51:00,426
even before lunchtime today.

1242
00:51:01,093 --> 00:51:02,060
Really?

1243
00:51:02,169 --> 00:51:06,502
I wanted to talk to you quickly,

1244
00:51:07,026 --> 00:51:10,326
but I could not create that situation,

1245
00:51:10,893 --> 00:51:15,493
and the fact
that it was not given to me...

1246
00:51:15,793 --> 00:51:18,426
made me feel frustrated.

1247
00:51:19,126 --> 00:51:22,326
I did not understand you at all,

1248
00:51:22,993 --> 00:51:24,160
and I barely knew you,

1249
00:51:24,160 --> 00:51:25,593
but I was just testing things.

1250
00:51:25,593 --> 00:51:28,060
You were just someone
who was only testing the waters with me.

1251
00:51:28,060 --> 00:51:29,826
Right?

1252
00:51:29,826 --> 00:51:31,893
So I thought,
"Is he like this with everyone?"

1253
00:51:31,893 --> 00:51:33,993
If we'd actually gone on a date
and talked,

1254
00:51:33,993 --> 00:51:37,626
I might have been able
to move to the next step,

1255
00:51:37,626 --> 00:51:40,993
but the situation did not allow it.

1256
00:51:41,493 --> 00:51:44,293
That is why my head has been hurting too.

1257
00:51:44,693 --> 00:51:46,860
He's more honest than I expected.

1258
00:51:51,360 --> 00:51:52,293
Is it my phone?

1259
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:55,160
Give me a second.

1260
00:51:56,060 --> 00:51:56,893
It's not mine.

1261
00:51:59,393 --> 00:52:01,926
She has to choose whether to extend
the date with her current partner...

1262
00:52:01,926 --> 00:52:03,609
or go on a date with someone else.

1263
00:52:05,926 --> 00:52:08,360
Do you think she'll extend her date
with him?

1264
00:52:08,360 --> 00:52:10,026
No, I don't think she will.

1265
00:52:10,326 --> 00:52:12,293
I think she'll want to go
on a date with someone else.

1266
00:52:12,293 --> 00:52:14,093
(Curious)

1267
00:52:15,060 --> 00:52:16,726
He's clueless now.

1268
00:52:16,726 --> 00:52:18,193
How could this...

1269
00:52:19,126 --> 00:52:23,226
(Other ladies received the same message.)

1270
00:52:25,226 --> 00:52:26,936
If she's with someone she doesn't want,

1271
00:52:26,960 --> 00:52:28,593
she'll definitely choose to go
on another date.

1272
00:52:31,460 --> 00:52:32,293
Oh.

1273
00:52:33,493 --> 00:52:35,208
Today really feels like a day
for the women.

1274
00:52:35,209 --> 00:52:36,393
(Who'll choose a new date?)

1275
00:52:36,826 --> 00:52:38,993
I don't think
she'll extend the date at all.

1276
00:52:39,626 --> 00:52:42,660
Every day is really making my heart race.

1277
00:52:43,193 --> 00:52:45,293
- That message always makes me nervous.
- I know, right?

1278
00:52:45,893 --> 00:52:47,693
- It really does.
- When I see my partner get that...

1279
00:52:47,693 --> 00:52:48,626
I agree.

1280
00:52:48,626 --> 00:52:50,326
(The younger men never know
the ladies' choice.)

1281
00:52:52,360 --> 00:52:54,393
(Smiling)

1282
00:52:56,393 --> 00:52:57,226
What?

1283
00:52:58,493 --> 00:53:00,193
It's time to say goodbye.

1284
00:53:00,826 --> 00:53:03,860
(We knew it.)

1285
00:53:03,860 --> 00:53:05,626
(Oh, my!)

1286
00:53:05,626 --> 00:53:07,226
It's time to say goodbye.

1287
00:53:08,493 --> 00:53:10,393
Suddenly? It makes me confused.

1288
00:53:11,226 --> 00:53:12,193
Okay.

1289
00:53:14,526 --> 00:53:15,826
It's been decided already.

1290
00:53:15,826 --> 00:53:16,826
(Shocked)

1291
00:53:18,026 --> 00:53:21,860
- I'm kidding.
- What? Wait.

1292
00:53:21,860 --> 00:53:23,893
- What?
- What was that?

1293
00:53:24,260 --> 00:53:26,693
- That was a joke.
- That was nice.

1294
00:53:26,693 --> 00:53:29,193
I just broke into a cold sweat.

1295
00:53:29,601 --> 00:53:31,735
I was told to choose someone
to go on a date with,

1296
00:53:31,760 --> 00:53:32,926
so I chose you.

1297
00:53:35,260 --> 00:53:36,226
What?

1298
00:53:36,226 --> 00:53:37,593
She wanted to go on a date with him.

1299
00:53:37,593 --> 00:53:38,393
Seriously?

1300
00:53:38,793 --> 00:53:39,926
So I chose you.

1301
00:53:41,493 --> 00:53:42,326
You like it, right?

1302
00:53:43,960 --> 00:53:46,460
- I love it.
- We haven't really talked much yet,

1303
00:53:47,260 --> 00:53:48,360
so I thought we should talk more.

1304
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:49,793
(She extended her date with him.)

1305
00:53:49,793 --> 00:53:51,126
I was really nervous just now.

1306
00:53:51,126 --> 00:53:54,160
- Did I make you nervous?
- Yes.

1307
00:53:54,926 --> 00:53:57,860
- Yes. You are the only one who made me...
- Were you flustered?

1308
00:53:57,860 --> 00:53:58,893
this flustered.

1309
00:53:59,693 --> 00:54:00,660
(Pleased)

1310
00:54:00,660 --> 00:54:02,126
That is exactly Jin Young's charm.

1311
00:54:02,126 --> 00:54:04,460
I didn't think of anything but a yes.

1312
00:54:04,460 --> 00:54:06,726
I wanted to go on a date with Jung Won.

1313
00:54:06,726 --> 00:54:08,226
I didn't think anything else.

1314
00:54:09,093 --> 00:54:11,026
So are we staying here all night today?

1315
00:54:11,026 --> 00:54:12,693
- Yes, let's stay out and enjoy the night.
- Sure.

1316
00:54:14,393 --> 00:54:18,293
(What did the other women choose?)

1317
00:54:18,660 --> 00:54:20,160
It's so interesting.

1318
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:22,560
I wonder what the other women have chosen.

1319
00:54:23,293 --> 00:54:27,560
(The extended date begins.)

1320
00:54:28,426 --> 00:54:31,760
(A wine bar with a great atmosphere,)

1321
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:35,993
(filled with various wines and whiskey,)

1322
00:54:37,160 --> 00:54:42,126
(is where the younger man
and woman are heading.)

1323
00:54:43,560 --> 00:54:46,060
(Ji Seung arrives first at the wine bar.)

1324
00:54:46,293 --> 00:54:48,560
(Did Ji Seung extend her date,
or is she waiting for a new younger man?)

1325
00:54:48,560 --> 00:54:51,293
I'm sure she picked Si Won.

1326
00:54:52,460 --> 00:54:57,560
(The younger man Ji Seung
is meeting at the wine bar is...)

1327
00:54:57,560 --> 00:55:00,160
(Jin Woo)

1328
00:55:00,160 --> 00:55:01,260
Really?

1329
00:55:01,260 --> 00:55:02,693
(Ji Seung extended her date?)

1330
00:55:05,560 --> 00:55:06,526
Good.

1331
00:55:06,526 --> 00:55:09,993
(Ji Seung extended her date with Jin Woo.)

1332
00:55:10,493 --> 00:55:14,326
I felt like we had
similar ways of thinking...

1333
00:55:14,760 --> 00:55:19,026
and similar mindsets,
so I sent a message saying yes.

1334
00:55:20,926 --> 00:55:23,326
Today feels like a really long date,
right?

1335
00:55:24,326 --> 00:55:26,760
He doesn't know
this date has been extended.

1336
00:55:27,560 --> 00:55:29,893
This is my first dinner date here.

1337
00:55:34,260 --> 00:55:35,126
Hold on.

1338
00:55:35,726 --> 00:55:37,360
- It's not mine.
- Maybe it's mine.

1339
00:55:37,893 --> 00:55:38,726
What?

1340
00:55:38,726 --> 00:55:42,693
(The message sent only to Jin Woo?)

1341
00:55:43,026 --> 00:55:44,760
(Surprised)

1342
00:55:45,793 --> 00:55:48,226
What is it?

1343
00:55:48,993 --> 00:55:51,060
Did you extend the date?

1344
00:55:51,060 --> 00:55:52,440
(Your date has extended
the date with you.)

1345
00:55:52,926 --> 00:55:55,093
What is written is probably right.

1346
00:55:55,093 --> 00:55:57,060
But why did they send it to you now?

1347
00:55:57,060 --> 00:55:58,460
(She shyly changes the subject.)

1348
00:55:58,960 --> 00:56:04,993
Now I see
that there was a reason for this.

1349
00:56:07,293 --> 00:56:09,393
He does not look very happy.

1350
00:56:12,460 --> 00:56:14,060
So,

1351
00:56:15,160 --> 00:56:17,360
did you choose me...

1352
00:56:18,093 --> 00:56:21,093
although you wanted to talk to other guys?

1353
00:56:21,760 --> 00:56:25,326
Or did you extend it because you didn't
want to get to know anyone else?

1354
00:56:25,893 --> 00:56:27,193
He wants to make sure of it.

1355
00:56:27,960 --> 00:56:33,293
We talked a lot in the car
and realized we had a lot in common.

1356
00:56:33,826 --> 00:56:36,893
So I guess this is an extension of that.

1357
00:56:37,860 --> 00:56:38,660
You know,

1358
00:56:40,226 --> 00:56:41,760
we don't know what will happen
in the future,

1359
00:56:42,226 --> 00:56:43,893
so I wanted to go on a date while we can.

1360
00:56:43,893 --> 00:56:45,926
- I see.
- Really?

1361
00:56:46,360 --> 00:56:47,193
Good.

1362
00:56:47,793 --> 00:56:51,760
(Ji Seung wanted to take time
to really get to know him.)

1363
00:56:52,326 --> 00:56:55,093
(On the other hand,
he did not show much reaction.)

1364
00:56:55,660 --> 00:56:57,026
- Let's dig in.
- Sure.

1365
00:56:57,993 --> 00:56:58,860
You're hungry, aren't you?

1366
00:57:01,226 --> 00:57:03,526
Can you be 100 percent honest with me?

1367
00:57:05,060 --> 00:57:06,126
- All of a sudden?
- Yes.

1368
00:57:06,893 --> 00:57:09,160
- One hundred percent?
- It's not like I can give you a heads-up.

1369
00:57:09,726 --> 00:57:12,360
I will try my best to be honest,

1370
00:57:12,360 --> 00:57:14,687
but from your perspective
it might not feel completely honest.

1371
00:57:18,326 --> 00:57:20,660
The date with me today was by coincidence.

1372
00:57:21,193 --> 00:57:22,860
- Yes.
- You didn't exactly choose me.

1373
00:57:23,193 --> 00:57:24,263
Right.

1374
00:57:24,793 --> 00:57:28,260
But extending it wasn't a coincidence,
but your choice.

1375
00:57:28,260 --> 00:57:31,393
(It started by coincidence
but continued with her choice.)

1376
00:57:31,693 --> 00:57:33,560
I'm not sure how you really feel yet.

1377
00:57:35,426 --> 00:57:36,460
That makes sense,

1378
00:57:37,026 --> 00:57:38,060
at this stage.

1379
00:57:38,060 --> 00:57:41,093
That's why I asked if you could
be completely honest with me.

1380
00:57:41,093 --> 00:57:43,893
(He's curious whether her feelings are
just curiosity or real.)

1381
00:57:43,893 --> 00:57:48,960
I came here to get to know people...

1382
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:51,060
I want to learn about anyway.

1383
00:57:51,360 --> 00:57:55,060
So for me, instead of rushing,

1384
00:57:55,060 --> 00:58:00,093
I think it's better to take enough time
and get to know several people.

1385
00:58:03,193 --> 00:58:05,326
Since I saw that message, my thoughts
have become really complicated.

1386
00:58:05,326 --> 00:58:06,126
Why?

1387
00:58:07,526 --> 00:58:09,793
You're not usually someone
who thinks this much.

1388
00:58:10,960 --> 00:58:12,726
You're mostly very clear-minded,
aren't you?

1389
00:58:15,126 --> 00:58:18,960
People can already tell
who I'm interested in...

1390
00:58:18,960 --> 00:58:21,626
because I express it pretty clearly.

1391
00:58:22,593 --> 00:58:26,326
But you still decided
to spend your day with me.

1392
00:58:26,326 --> 00:58:29,226
It was partly choice
and partly coincidence, but still.

1393
00:58:29,226 --> 00:58:30,760
Right.

1394
00:58:31,626 --> 00:58:36,293
I've experienced situations
where my mood changed...

1395
00:58:36,293 --> 00:58:38,926
depending
on the reactions of someone I liked.

1396
00:58:39,593 --> 00:58:41,726
And because of my actions or choices,

1397
00:58:43,260 --> 00:58:47,060
I might end up
hurting someone else's feelings.

1398
00:58:48,693 --> 00:58:50,760
I really don't want that to happen.

1399
00:58:51,926 --> 00:58:53,526
It concerns him.

1400
00:58:53,526 --> 00:58:55,060
(He's worried that his feelings for Ji Hye
might hurt her.)

1401
00:58:59,850 --> 00:59:01,526
But I think...

1402
00:59:02,993 --> 00:59:04,626
it's better...

1403
00:59:05,660 --> 00:59:07,793
- to follow your feelings.
- I agree.

1404
00:59:10,926 --> 00:59:14,726
It's better not to leave
any regrets behind.

1405
00:59:14,726 --> 00:59:18,126
(Even after hearing his feelings,
she remains calm.)

1406
00:59:18,826 --> 00:59:23,060
I just want to get to know the guys
in my own way.

1407
00:59:23,693 --> 00:59:26,493
Jin Woo clearly has feelings for Ji Hye,

1408
00:59:27,193 --> 00:59:30,226
so I just wanted to spend
the date time with him properly.

1409
00:59:30,226 --> 00:59:35,493
And through that date, I realized clearly
that he wasn't the right match for me.

1410
00:59:36,326 --> 00:59:39,726
So I think it was a very satisfying time.

1411
00:59:39,726 --> 00:59:41,793
I feel like I had to get to know
as much as I could...

1412
00:59:42,426 --> 00:59:46,326
in order to make a decision
without regrets,

1413
00:59:48,493 --> 00:59:52,160
so I think this was actually better for me
than two days ago.

1414
00:59:53,760 --> 00:59:58,193
- So Jin Woo still likes Ji Hye,
- Exactly.

1415
00:59:58,193 --> 01:00:01,360
but he might also be starting
to feel something for Ji Seung,

1416
01:00:01,360 --> 01:00:04,060
so it feels like she drew a line with him.

1417
01:00:04,490 --> 01:00:07,826
But actually, he doesn't need
to overthink it.

1418
01:00:07,827 --> 01:00:10,361
(Their Extended Date grows heavy
with deep thoughts.)

1419
01:00:10,563 --> 01:00:12,931
(Jin Young and Jung Won's Extended Date)

1420
01:00:12,932 --> 01:00:14,366
This place is nice.

1421
01:00:14,367 --> 01:00:15,433
I know.

1422
01:00:17,736 --> 01:00:20,037
Oddly enough, I don't even feel hungry.

1423
01:00:20,038 --> 01:00:21,539
Yes. Do you remember?

1424
01:00:21,540 --> 01:00:23,741
I went out because I was starving...

1425
01:00:23,742 --> 01:00:25,810
and it was so early in the morning,
I felt nauseous.

1426
01:00:25,811 --> 01:00:29,280
- When?
- When you made that egg soy sauce rice.

1427
01:00:29,281 --> 01:00:30,614
When I cooked for you?

1428
01:00:31,617 --> 01:00:34,385
- Really?
- I was starving.

1429
01:00:37,156 --> 01:00:39,424
I thought you made that up
just to have an excuse to talk to me.

1430
01:00:39,425 --> 01:00:40,558
No, seriously.

1431
01:00:40,759 --> 01:00:42,694
The timing was crazy.

1432
01:00:42,828 --> 01:00:44,762
Everything just lined up perfectly.

1433
01:00:45,998 --> 01:00:49,968
(Jung Won ran into Jin Young by chance
when he went out to get food.)

1434
01:00:49,969 --> 01:00:53,038
- There is nobody else in the room.
- Really?

1435
01:00:53,739 --> 01:00:55,808
I think I want...

1436
01:00:56,408 --> 01:00:57,776
to talk to you more tomorrow.

1437
01:00:59,708 --> 01:01:00,545
With me?

1438
01:01:00,546 --> 01:01:01,412
Yes.

1439
01:01:01,413 --> 01:01:02,347
Do you want to talk now?

1440
01:01:03,115 --> 01:01:03,948
That's right.

1441
01:01:04,316 --> 01:01:07,618
(Their first time alone together)

1442
01:01:08,196 --> 01:01:10,764
I wonder why.
Did a lot of things just line up?

1443
01:01:10,789 --> 01:01:12,089
(And their date continues.)

1444
01:01:12,090 --> 01:01:13,291
I don't know.

1445
01:01:13,292 --> 01:01:14,192
Here you go.

1446
01:01:14,193 --> 01:01:17,328
(Food is served as they talk.)

1447
01:01:17,329 --> 01:01:18,696
Thank you.

1448
01:01:18,697 --> 01:01:20,565
- Should we take pictures?
- Sure.

1449
01:01:22,034 --> 01:01:22,967
One, two...

1450
01:01:23,769 --> 01:01:27,405
(Their first picture
with just the two of them)

1451
01:01:27,406 --> 01:01:28,339
One more?

1452
01:01:30,042 --> 01:01:31,442
- Okay. Looks good.
- Good.

1453
01:01:31,443 --> 01:01:32,310
Want to see?

1454
01:01:33,512 --> 01:01:34,512
It turned out great.

1455
01:01:35,147 --> 01:01:36,080
I like them.

1456
01:01:36,348 --> 01:01:37,415
I like it.

1457
01:01:37,416 --> 01:01:38,349
They look good together.

1458
01:01:38,484 --> 01:01:39,885
- Great picture.
- It came out well.

1459
01:01:40,519 --> 01:01:42,687
- Let's eat now.
- Let's eat.

1460
01:01:42,688 --> 01:01:43,754
Bon appetit.

1461
01:01:44,957 --> 01:01:46,558
- Go ahead.
- Where should we start?

1462
01:01:48,093 --> 01:01:49,360
(Cheers)

1463
01:01:52,364 --> 01:01:53,497
This is so good.

1464
01:01:53,832 --> 01:01:55,432
(Refreshing)

1465
01:01:56,669 --> 01:01:58,103
I feel alive again.

1466
01:01:59,004 --> 01:01:59,803
(Both excited)

1467
01:01:59,804 --> 01:02:02,239
I should be talking, but I keep eating.

1468
01:02:02,240 --> 01:02:03,742
It's literally ASMR right now.

1469
01:02:09,014 --> 01:02:09,981
- What?
- What?

1470
01:02:10,995 --> 01:02:14,297
(Someone is here.)

1471
01:02:14,486 --> 01:02:15,453
It's Ji Hye!

1472
01:02:16,088 --> 01:02:17,488
(Both excited by the good food and drinks)

1473
01:02:17,489 --> 01:02:19,458
It's literally ASMR right now.

1474
01:02:25,030 --> 01:02:25,896
- What?
- What?

1475
01:02:26,899 --> 01:02:30,335
(Someone is here.)

1476
01:02:30,436 --> 01:02:31,469
It's Ji Hye!

1477
01:02:32,671 --> 01:02:35,606
(Someone approaches the two of them.)

1478
01:02:37,009 --> 01:02:37,809
- What?
- What?

1479
01:02:38,410 --> 01:02:39,074
What?

1480
01:02:39,099 --> 01:02:40,411
- Yu Jin?
- What?

1481
01:02:45,951 --> 01:02:48,252
- Oh my goodness, look at her face.
- What?

1482
01:02:48,587 --> 01:02:49,620
Look at her face!

1483
01:02:49,655 --> 01:02:51,255
I love this!

1484
01:02:51,256 --> 01:02:52,457
Splash some water on her!

1485
01:02:53,025 --> 01:02:54,191
Why would she do that?

1486
01:02:54,192 --> 01:02:55,861
- So she can taste it!
- What's with you?

1487
01:02:55,862 --> 01:02:57,996
- Yu Jin, try it! It's good!
- What's wrong with you?

1488
01:02:57,997 --> 01:02:59,030
Protect Yu Jin!

1489
01:02:59,364 --> 01:03:00,664
This drink is amazing!

1490
01:03:00,833 --> 01:03:02,066
Oh my gosh!

1491
01:03:02,067 --> 01:03:04,135
(What is going on here?)

1492
01:03:07,106 --> 01:03:07,972
What's happening?

1493
01:03:10,442 --> 01:03:12,710
Huh? What's going on?

1494
01:03:13,846 --> 01:03:14,813
(Yu Jin arrives at their date venue.)

1495
01:03:14,838 --> 01:03:16,348
Have a seat!

1496
01:03:18,317 --> 01:03:19,284
What's going on?

1497
01:03:21,687 --> 01:03:22,821
Have a seat!

1498
01:03:23,756 --> 01:03:25,657
- Have a seat!
- What's going on?

1499
01:03:27,493 --> 01:03:30,361
All of a sudden? I'm so shocked.
Have a seat.

1500
01:03:30,593 --> 01:03:33,364
But what... what were you doing?

1501
01:03:34,900 --> 01:03:36,100
I was on a date.

1502
01:03:36,101 --> 01:03:38,069
- Did you come here by yourself?
- Yes.

1503
01:03:39,071 --> 01:03:40,471
Who were you on a date with?

1504
01:03:40,472 --> 01:03:42,407
I was with Yun So.

1505
01:03:42,908 --> 01:03:45,042
(Yu Jin chose not to extend
her date with Yun So.)

1506
01:03:45,043 --> 01:03:46,577
- Wait.
- Hold on.

1507
01:03:46,779 --> 01:03:47,645
Wait.

1508
01:03:47,646 --> 01:03:49,547
Is someone else coming?

1509
01:03:49,548 --> 01:03:50,682
That could happen.

1510
01:03:50,683 --> 01:03:52,817
(Finally understanding
what the Extended Date means.)

1511
01:03:52,818 --> 01:03:54,619
Nice to see you.

1512
01:03:54,620 --> 01:03:57,155
(The women can choose to see
a different younger man.)

1513
01:03:57,156 --> 01:03:58,512
Do you want to order anything?

1514
01:03:58,537 --> 01:03:59,258
Here.

1515
01:04:00,292 --> 01:04:02,627
I heard the food is good here.

1516
01:04:02,961 --> 01:04:04,930
Talk about a reality check.

1517
01:04:05,397 --> 01:04:08,500
I felt like this can't be right.

1518
01:04:09,568 --> 01:04:13,404
Yu Jin showing up
out of nowhere like that?

1519
01:04:13,405 --> 01:04:15,606
I was completely shocked.

1520
01:04:16,175 --> 01:04:17,709
I was totally shocked.

1521
01:04:19,344 --> 01:04:20,344
(Sending Jung Won into a state of shock)

1522
01:04:20,345 --> 01:04:21,845
The war has begun.

1523
01:04:23,115 --> 01:04:26,017
When we talked
in the Talk Room yesterday...

1524
01:04:27,152 --> 01:04:30,421
- We need to talk to other people.
- Have more conversations.

1525
01:04:30,422 --> 01:04:32,456
You and I should go on a date too.

1526
01:04:34,359 --> 01:04:37,029
I was curious
about going on a casual date...

1527
01:04:37,395 --> 01:04:40,399
instead of diving
into a deep conversation right away.

1528
01:04:41,633 --> 01:04:44,702
So I texted that I'll be going
on a date with Jung Won.

1529
01:04:53,779 --> 01:04:55,480
- Back at the house?
- Yes.

1530
01:04:56,390 --> 01:04:58,048
But where did Yun So...

1531
01:04:58,150 --> 01:05:00,250
- Yun So wouldn't know.
- Where did Yun So go?

1532
01:05:00,251 --> 01:05:01,853
I don't know.

1533
01:05:01,854 --> 01:05:04,021
- Oh, you don't know.
- No, we don't.

1534
01:05:04,690 --> 01:05:06,423
But didn't they...

1535
01:05:06,992 --> 01:05:08,259
During your date...

1536
01:05:09,361 --> 01:05:12,164
didn't they ask
if you wanted to extend it?

1537
01:05:12,631 --> 01:05:14,131
I chose you.

1538
01:05:16,668 --> 01:05:18,002
Look at Mr. Popular.

1539
01:05:18,737 --> 01:05:20,037
Ever so popular.

1540
01:05:20,038 --> 01:05:22,573
I wanted to try going
on an outdoor date like this.

1541
01:05:23,208 --> 01:05:26,344
Oh, my. I should probably
leave you two alone.

1542
01:05:27,212 --> 01:05:29,080
(Will you, really?)

1543
01:05:29,081 --> 01:05:30,382
You want me to go?

1544
01:05:31,016 --> 01:05:32,350
- Do you want me to?
- You can stay.

1545
01:05:32,618 --> 01:05:34,319
- Gosh.
- Let's see.

1546
01:05:35,654 --> 01:05:38,456
- Then I'll get... Yours is a highball?
- Yes, a highball.

1547
01:05:38,457 --> 01:05:39,857
Do you want the same thing?

1548
01:05:40,759 --> 01:05:41,592
Yes.

1549
01:05:41,794 --> 01:05:44,061
- Can we get another one?
- Make it less sweet.

1550
01:05:44,062 --> 01:05:45,263
Less sweet, please.

1551
01:05:46,031 --> 01:05:47,698
Could we get
another place setting as well?

1552
01:05:47,699 --> 01:05:49,267
Could you set the table
for one more person?

1553
01:05:52,304 --> 01:05:54,338
This is so intense!

1554
01:05:54,740 --> 01:05:56,274
Calm down, Jin Young...

1555
01:05:57,448 --> 01:05:58,815
- Could you put this next to you?
- Okay.

1556
01:06:00,712 --> 01:06:02,846
Is Yun So back at the house then?

1557
01:06:03,282 --> 01:06:07,352
Is Yun So back at the house by himself?

1558
01:06:07,353 --> 01:06:08,887
No, maybe he went somewhere else.

1559
01:06:08,888 --> 01:06:09,721
I see.

1560
01:06:09,722 --> 01:06:12,190
Someone else might have summoned him.

1561
01:06:12,191 --> 01:06:13,057
Yes.

1562
01:06:13,058 --> 01:06:14,158
But anyway,

1563
01:06:14,493 --> 01:06:16,060
you're here now.

1564
01:06:16,061 --> 01:06:18,496
At least someone will be back
at the house.

1565
01:06:18,497 --> 01:06:20,331
- Yes, that's true.
- Right?

1566
01:06:20,332 --> 01:06:22,066
Who did you go on a date with first?

1567
01:06:22,467 --> 01:06:24,736
- With me.
- Oh, you extended it!

1568
01:06:24,737 --> 01:06:26,938
We got in the car together at first.

1569
01:06:28,173 --> 01:06:29,340
Oh, I see.

1570
01:06:30,475 --> 01:06:31,708
Thank you.

1571
01:06:33,278 --> 01:06:35,412
- Should we cheers then?
- Sure.

1572
01:06:36,057 --> 01:06:37,791
- I'm glad you're here.
- Glad to have you.

1573
01:06:37,816 --> 01:06:39,850
I feel like a third wheel.

1574
01:06:39,851 --> 01:06:41,252
- Not at all.
- It's fun.

1575
01:06:41,920 --> 01:06:42,887
What?

1576
01:06:43,522 --> 01:06:45,056
- It's fun for me too.
- Right?

1577
01:06:45,057 --> 01:06:46,891
This just got very interesting.

1578
01:06:46,892 --> 01:06:48,693
This is crazy. She's fuming.

1579
01:06:49,461 --> 01:06:50,561
(Spilling)

1580
01:06:55,167 --> 01:06:58,002
He used to look after her,
but not anymore!

1581
01:06:58,937 --> 01:06:59,803
(Glancing)

1582
01:06:59,804 --> 01:07:01,906
- This is good.
- Yes, it is.

1583
01:07:03,676 --> 01:07:04,676
I was annoyed.

1584
01:07:05,177 --> 01:07:06,744
Yu Jin showed up.

1585
01:07:07,079 --> 01:07:08,479
And the moment she did,

1586
01:07:08,480 --> 01:07:10,448
he completely tuned me out.

1587
01:07:11,683 --> 01:07:13,384
I mean, look at him.

1588
01:07:14,353 --> 01:07:17,155
He never shows
that he's interested in me...

1589
01:07:17,489 --> 01:07:18,957
when other people are around.

1590
01:07:20,025 --> 01:07:21,359
Is that fun for him?

1591
01:07:24,830 --> 01:07:25,763
This is nice.

1592
01:07:25,998 --> 01:07:27,432
Did you have fun with Yun So?

1593
01:07:27,433 --> 01:07:29,667
- Oh, yes. I did.
- Wasn't it...

1594
01:07:29,668 --> 01:07:31,636
- your first date with him?
- It was.

1595
01:07:31,637 --> 01:07:32,437
So,

1596
01:07:32,771 --> 01:07:35,573
when we picked the Charm Card...

1597
01:07:35,574 --> 01:07:37,608
I was like, "As long as it's not Yun So."

1598
01:07:37,609 --> 01:07:38,743
That's what I said.

1599
01:07:39,311 --> 01:07:41,746
I thought, "It'll be bad if it's Yun So."

1600
01:07:41,747 --> 01:07:42,647
- Really?
- Yes.

1601
01:07:42,648 --> 01:07:44,783
Why? Did you feel uncomfortable?

1602
01:07:44,784 --> 01:07:45,950
Were you not interested?

1603
01:07:45,951 --> 01:07:48,619
No, it's just that up until now...

1604
01:07:48,820 --> 01:07:51,522
Yun So has been completely single-minded.

1605
01:07:51,523 --> 01:07:53,490
Through this date, I wanted to see...

1606
01:07:53,759 --> 01:07:59,964
if there was any potential
with someone else.

1607
01:08:00,198 --> 01:08:02,533
And I figured that would be hard
to find with Yun So.

1608
01:08:02,534 --> 01:08:04,501
- Because he's so set in his ways.
- Yes.

1609
01:08:04,502 --> 01:08:06,003
What did the card say?

1610
01:08:06,004 --> 01:08:08,505
It said, "very talkative."

1611
01:08:09,408 --> 01:08:11,209
- And a good...
- Listener?

1612
01:08:11,210 --> 01:08:12,310
Yes. A good listener.

1613
01:08:12,311 --> 01:08:14,245
So I thought it was you.

1614
01:08:14,246 --> 01:08:15,613
I thought it was you.

1615
01:08:15,614 --> 01:08:17,248
You thought it was me?

1616
01:08:18,450 --> 01:08:20,117
- Nice!
- Straight to the point!

1617
01:08:20,118 --> 01:08:22,019
Let's go!

1618
01:08:22,020 --> 01:08:23,788
She just went right in!

1619
01:08:23,789 --> 01:08:25,990
She caught him completely off guard!

1620
01:08:27,226 --> 01:08:28,726
I thought it was you.

1621
01:08:28,727 --> 01:08:30,261
You thought it was me?

1622
01:08:30,762 --> 01:08:31,929
You thought it was me?

1623
01:08:33,665 --> 01:08:35,132
"I'm a good listener"?

1624
01:08:35,967 --> 01:08:37,735
A good listener is...

1625
01:08:37,736 --> 01:08:39,737
It says he's talkative too.

1626
01:08:39,738 --> 01:08:42,572
Then, isn't this Jung Won?

1627
01:08:43,509 --> 01:08:46,710
Talkative, but is he a good listener?

1628
01:08:46,945 --> 01:08:48,979
- He is.
- He is?

1629
01:08:50,883 --> 01:08:52,651
You thought it was me?

1630
01:08:53,952 --> 01:08:55,819
Yes. What did yours say?

1631
01:08:56,221 --> 01:09:00,958
It was something like making you feel
constantly happy and content.

1632
01:09:01,359 --> 01:09:04,394
No. It's fun to be around.

1633
01:09:04,395 --> 01:09:07,464
And happy when we're doing
something together.

1634
01:09:07,999 --> 01:09:08,932
I see.

1635
01:09:09,368 --> 01:09:11,437
So I think it worked out well.

1636
01:09:11,438 --> 01:09:13,103
After going on a date with Yun So,

1637
01:09:13,104 --> 01:09:16,407
I feel like my feelings became clear.

1638
01:09:19,511 --> 01:09:20,444
In what way?

1639
01:09:20,846 --> 01:09:22,379
- Is it a secret?
- It is.

1640
01:09:24,850 --> 01:09:26,651
We took pictures, and it was fun.

1641
01:09:28,787 --> 01:09:29,955
We had fun too.

1642
01:09:29,956 --> 01:09:30,888
Yes.

1643
01:09:30,889 --> 01:09:32,690
It was fun, right?

1644
01:09:32,958 --> 01:09:35,726
We went to the alpaca farm.

1645
01:09:36,561 --> 01:09:38,096
And time just flew by.

1646
01:09:38,730 --> 01:09:42,000
I like that kind of stuff too.
Feeding alpacas and everything.

1647
01:09:42,501 --> 01:09:44,335
Yes. So...

1648
01:09:44,903 --> 01:09:46,770
I heard Yun So did your hair today.

1649
01:09:46,938 --> 01:09:48,171
He told you that?

1650
01:09:50,108 --> 01:09:51,008
(At a time like this?)

1651
01:09:51,009 --> 01:09:54,011
Oh my gosh!

1652
01:09:54,613 --> 01:09:56,246
Oh my goodness!

1653
01:09:56,581 --> 01:09:57,882
Yu Jin is unbelievable.

1654
01:09:59,050 --> 01:10:01,652
- She's going on the attack!
- Incredible.

1655
01:10:01,920 --> 01:10:04,788
"I was going to play nice.
But you started this."

1656
01:10:04,801 --> 01:10:06,424
She struck right back.

1657
01:10:06,434 --> 01:10:07,529
(Yu Jin doesn't hold back.)

1658
01:10:07,689 --> 01:10:09,609
I heard Yun So did your hair today.

1659
01:10:09,842 --> 01:10:11,372
Did he really say that?

1660
01:10:12,449 --> 01:10:14,875
- I was trying to keep that a secret.
- Really?

1661
01:10:15,375 --> 01:10:16,877
How is it? Do you like it?

1662
01:10:17,649 --> 01:10:18,712
Do you like it?

1663
01:10:19,142 --> 01:10:21,222
Yes, I like it.

1664
01:10:21,929 --> 01:10:24,809
I was trying to keep that a secret.

1665
01:10:25,335 --> 01:10:27,020
Did I just make
a massive slip of the tongue?

1666
01:10:27,045 --> 01:10:28,095
No.

1667
01:10:28,260 --> 01:10:31,137
It's just that if the others hear,
they might misunderstand.

1668
01:10:31,161 --> 01:10:33,382
I just didn't feel like doing my hair.

1669
01:10:33,406 --> 01:10:35,810
So I asked him to add some volume,
that's all.

1670
01:10:36,065 --> 01:10:37,415
Whatever the case.

1671
01:10:37,440 --> 01:10:39,804
She really knows
how to throw jabs with a smile.

1672
01:10:40,908 --> 01:10:42,302
That's wild.

1673
01:10:43,296 --> 01:10:44,872
I was sitting on pins and needles.

1674
01:10:45,822 --> 01:10:47,941
I was so flustered.

1675
01:10:48,692 --> 01:10:51,252
(A risky drink shared among the three)

1676
01:10:51,389 --> 01:10:53,714
Who have you been on dates with so far?

1677
01:10:53,849 --> 01:10:57,947
For me, Yun So and Jun Han.

1678
01:10:57,971 --> 01:11:00,009
And I talked to Jung Won yesterday.
That was yesterday, right?

1679
01:11:00,010 --> 01:11:01,684
- That's right, yesterday.
- We talked.

1680
01:11:01,709 --> 01:11:03,469
You two went to the Talk Room yesterday.

1681
01:11:03,494 --> 01:11:05,726
I completely forgot about that.

1682
01:11:07,535 --> 01:11:09,763
But you probably didn't expect us
to be here right now.

1683
01:11:10,082 --> 01:11:11,763
For some reason, though,

1684
01:11:11,788 --> 01:11:18,246
I thought the woman with Jung Won
might keep it going.

1685
01:11:21,049 --> 01:11:22,242
Hold on.

1686
01:11:22,302 --> 01:11:23,101
What's that?

1687
01:11:23,968 --> 01:11:25,068
Is someone else coming?

1688
01:11:25,589 --> 01:11:26,880
- I knew it.
- What is it?

1689
01:11:29,614 --> 01:11:30,685
That's crazy.

1690
01:11:31,466 --> 01:11:32,152
Again?

1691
01:11:33,095 --> 01:11:34,659
(The third older woman appears.)

1692
01:11:34,845 --> 01:11:35,947
Bravo.

1693
01:11:36,025 --> 01:11:38,092
He just ran his tongue over his teeth.

1694
01:11:40,122 --> 01:11:41,495
- I knew it.
- What is it?

1695
01:11:44,102 --> 01:11:45,242
That's crazy.

1696
01:11:48,413 --> 01:11:49,403
Hi.

1697
01:11:49,428 --> 01:11:52,214
(Ju Hee, the third older woman
who chose Jung Won)

1698
01:11:52,787 --> 01:11:54,611
(Ju Hee?)

1699
01:11:54,811 --> 01:11:55,876
What?

1700
01:11:56,639 --> 01:11:57,411
Ju Hee?

1701
01:11:57,594 --> 01:11:58,678
- What?
- Ju Hee, seriously?

1702
01:11:59,218 --> 01:12:01,315
This is driving me crazy.

1703
01:12:02,218 --> 01:12:03,083
Hi.

1704
01:12:03,129 --> 01:12:07,474
(Ju Hee makes an unexpected appearance.)

1705
01:12:11,888 --> 01:12:12,659
Seriously?

1706
01:12:18,799 --> 01:12:23,336
(Ju Hee came to Jung Won
without extending her date with Jun Han.)

1707
01:12:24,722 --> 01:12:26,273
No, how did this...

1708
01:12:26,475 --> 01:12:27,145
(Restless)

1709
01:12:27,170 --> 01:12:28,709
- Why?
- You seriously scared me.

1710
01:12:28,765 --> 01:12:31,089
I kept thinking, "There's no way
another person is coming."

1711
01:12:31,114 --> 01:12:32,704
- Excuse me.
- And then you actually showed up.

1712
01:12:34,379 --> 01:12:35,282
This is fun.

1713
01:12:36,339 --> 01:12:40,099
When I looked at Jung Won,
putting romantic interest aside,

1714
01:12:40,152 --> 01:12:41,152
I was curious about him.

1715
01:12:41,177 --> 01:12:43,612
I wanted to try talking to him,

1716
01:12:43,636 --> 01:12:45,726
so I think I just wanted to spend
some time with him.

1717
01:12:48,312 --> 01:12:49,821
It's hot in here, isn't it?

1718
01:12:57,119 --> 01:12:58,505
I wanted to get a bit closer to Jung Won.

1719
01:12:58,530 --> 01:12:59,840
I mean, honestly...

1720
01:13:00,165 --> 01:13:04,199
I probably talked to you the least
out of everyone in the house.

1721
01:13:04,265 --> 01:13:06,328
Because we kept sitting so far apart.

1722
01:13:06,368 --> 01:13:07,114
Right.

1723
01:13:07,412 --> 01:13:10,317
It felt like being on that island
I mentioned earlier.

1724
01:13:11,436 --> 01:13:13,339
- Like, "It's just too far."
- Right.

1725
01:13:14,059 --> 01:13:15,814
Conversation is so important.

1726
01:13:15,839 --> 01:13:17,024
Right.

1727
01:13:17,579 --> 01:13:19,560
Is there anyone else you want to talk to?

1728
01:13:19,799 --> 01:13:21,362
I wanted to try talking to Jung Won.

1729
01:13:24,039 --> 01:13:26,667
Are you originally from Seoul?

1730
01:13:26,799 --> 01:13:28,599
Originally Seongbuk-gu, Seoul.

1731
01:13:28,624 --> 01:13:30,739
- Do you live alone, or with your family?
- With my family.

1732
01:13:32,499 --> 01:13:36,439
But where do you give
your gayageum lessons then?

1733
01:13:36,492 --> 01:13:38,597
I go to the students' houses for lessons.

1734
01:13:39,085 --> 01:13:41,581
I don't run an academy.

1735
01:13:41,798 --> 01:13:43,510
So it feels more like 1-on-1 coaching.

1736
01:13:43,535 --> 01:13:46,152
Actually, in a way, the gayageum is...

1737
01:13:46,610 --> 01:13:50,157
something you have to teach
strictly 1-on-1.

1738
01:13:50,659 --> 01:13:54,461
Teaching a large group
wouldn't be easy, right?

1739
01:13:55,632 --> 01:13:57,698
Those two are completely
sidelined right now.

1740
01:13:58,178 --> 01:13:59,617
Do you have a lot of students?
Or just a select few?

1741
01:13:59,642 --> 01:14:01,226
- Should we all talk together?
- Just a select few.

1742
01:14:01,401 --> 01:14:02,914
(They try to participate
in the conversation.)

1743
01:14:02,939 --> 01:14:04,037
Go ahead and talk.

1744
01:14:04,257 --> 01:14:05,639
Come on.

1745
01:14:05,821 --> 01:14:06,519
I'm sorry.

1746
01:14:06,543 --> 01:14:07,879
You two go ahead and talk
so I can talk too.

1747
01:14:07,904 --> 01:14:09,176
Do you want to talk to Ju Hee alone?

1748
01:14:09,201 --> 01:14:11,078
I was just asking about a few things
I was curious about.

1749
01:14:11,103 --> 01:14:11,870
I see.

1750
01:14:14,167 --> 01:14:16,490
(Awkward)

1751
01:14:22,489 --> 01:14:25,189
You must have a high alcohol tolerance.

1752
01:14:25,346 --> 01:14:26,159
- Me?
- Yes.

1753
01:14:28,122 --> 01:14:31,022
It's not that high,
but I can hold my liquor.

1754
01:14:31,209 --> 01:14:33,930
If there's a gathering with drinks,
you don't back out and just drink?

1755
01:14:33,955 --> 01:14:36,803
But if I feel a little tipsy,
I pace myself right away.

1756
01:14:37,755 --> 01:14:40,674
Because I can usually tell
when I'm getting drunk.

1757
01:14:40,699 --> 01:14:42,051
(Jung Won keeps firing questions
at Ju Hee.)

1758
01:14:42,076 --> 01:14:44,004
- Are you tipsy right now? Are you okay?
- Right now?

1759
01:14:44,029 --> 01:14:45,579
Right now, I'm getting a little tipsy.

1760
01:14:46,095 --> 01:14:48,182
Your face did get a bit flushed.

1761
01:14:48,207 --> 01:14:49,908
No, you're redder right now.

1762
01:14:50,442 --> 01:14:52,653
I'm getting tipsy kind of fast.

1763
01:14:52,829 --> 01:14:55,189
Your face turns red quickly.

1764
01:14:55,489 --> 01:14:57,691
I don't know why I'm getting tipsy now.

1765
01:14:59,395 --> 01:15:01,064
Because you're in a good mood.

1766
01:15:01,089 --> 01:15:02,649
A good mood, I guess.

1767
01:15:04,689 --> 01:15:06,149
This isn't easy.

1768
01:15:10,281 --> 01:15:13,727
They came to have
a 1-on-1 conversation with me too,

1769
01:15:13,752 --> 01:15:15,878
but that kind of atmosphere
just couldn't be formed.

1770
01:15:15,903 --> 01:15:18,511
So honestly, it didn't feel like a date.

1771
01:15:18,848 --> 01:15:20,168
A confusing date.

1772
01:15:20,315 --> 01:15:21,675
A chaotic date.

1773
01:15:21,915 --> 01:15:23,183
That's what it felt like.

1774
01:15:26,476 --> 01:15:28,489
Why is the wind blowing so hard?

1775
01:15:28,514 --> 01:15:30,618
(Ji Hye arrives at the Extended Date
location at that exact moment.)

1776
01:15:30,642 --> 01:15:32,993
No way, please don't let it be her.

1777
01:15:34,673 --> 01:15:37,421
(Jung Won again?)

1778
01:15:37,549 --> 01:15:40,033
Surely no one else is coming, right?

1779
01:15:41,416 --> 01:15:42,949
- You never know.
- You never know.

1780
01:15:43,015 --> 01:15:45,141
- You never know.
- You never know.

1781
01:15:45,166 --> 01:15:45,829
You never know.

1782
01:15:45,854 --> 01:15:47,207
Who's left?

1783
01:15:47,232 --> 01:15:48,265
(Drained)

1784
01:15:49,249 --> 01:15:54,054
(Which younger man
is Ji Hye heading toward?)

1785
01:15:54,079 --> 01:15:56,249
- Surely it's not him.
- No way.

1786
01:15:56,638 --> 01:15:59,619
If it turns out to be him,
that's four women coming for Jung Won.

1787
01:15:59,887 --> 01:16:03,834
(Next episode)

1788
01:16:03,859 --> 01:16:05,784
"Please come out
to the front yard of the QR Room..."

1789
01:16:05,808 --> 01:16:07,139
"and sit wherever you like on the chairs."

1790
01:16:07,159 --> 01:16:08,495
In front of the QR Room?

1791
01:16:08,729 --> 01:16:12,118
(The moment to face each other's real age
has finally arrived.)

1792
01:16:12,290 --> 01:16:15,435
I was born in...

1793
01:16:17,559 --> 01:16:20,307
I thought, "He's so young."

1794
01:16:20,338 --> 01:16:22,609
I was born in...

1795
01:16:23,671 --> 01:16:26,046
- Really?
- Hold on.

1796
01:16:26,125 --> 01:16:27,881
You look so young for your age.

1797
01:16:28,906 --> 01:16:31,919
Hearing and facing the actual age
made it feel real.

1798
01:16:32,317 --> 01:16:34,274
I had a bit of a mental breakdown,

1799
01:16:34,299 --> 01:16:35,555
wondering what I should do.

1800
01:16:36,732 --> 01:16:39,026
Do you see a future for us?

1801
01:16:39,140 --> 01:16:40,761
No, I can't see it.

1802
01:16:41,412 --> 01:16:45,892
But I've been thinking about you
a lot since yesterday too.

1803
01:16:46,438 --> 01:16:47,467
- Really?
- Yes.

1804
01:16:49,979 --> 01:16:51,271
I'm completely sorted out.

1805
01:16:51,398 --> 01:16:52,539
My mind is made up now.

1806
01:16:52,564 --> 01:16:53,507
I'm all done.

1807
01:16:53,778 --> 01:16:55,341
Today's age reveal,

1808
01:16:55,825 --> 01:16:58,345
did it affect your decision at all?

1809
01:16:58,398 --> 01:17:00,814
I didn't think you would care
about age at all.

1810
01:17:01,251 --> 01:17:02,081
Just leave already.

1811
01:17:02,439 --> 01:17:03,250
Just leave.

1812
01:17:03,699 --> 01:17:06,692
(The intense war of nerves
between Jin Woo and Jung Won over Ji Hye)

1813
01:17:07,025 --> 01:17:09,559
- I talked quite a bit with Ji Seung.
- Right.

1814
01:17:09,584 --> 01:17:12,484
So I've figured things out to some extent.

1815
01:17:12,832 --> 01:17:15,829
But I also really wanted to talk to you.

1816
01:17:15,845 --> 01:17:18,112
(And Si Won and Yu Jin are starting
to get to know each other.)

1817
01:17:18,137 --> 01:17:21,568
Honestly, talking to Si Won right now...

1818
01:17:21,593 --> 01:17:22,469
Right.

1819
01:17:22,605 --> 01:17:25,196
It's funny to be talking to Si Won
out of nowhere at this hour.

1820
01:17:25,625 --> 01:17:28,645
I felt like the conversation with Si Won
went much better than expected.

1821
01:17:28,706 --> 01:17:30,666
In just a few hours?

1822
01:17:31,592 --> 01:17:34,147
Then are you going straight to Si Won now?

1823
01:17:34,172 --> 01:17:36,712
I think that's how it's going
to turn out for me.

1824
01:17:37,452 --> 01:17:41,388
Honestly, I was a bit surprised
when you said that early this morning.

1825
01:17:41,905 --> 01:17:43,924
It wasn't exactly aggressive.

1826
01:17:44,359 --> 01:17:46,560
You said it while being mindful of things.

1827
01:17:47,406 --> 01:17:49,263
Why did you say it
like a declaration of war?

1828
01:17:49,532 --> 01:17:51,698
I didn't mean it as a declaration of war.

1829
01:17:52,132 --> 01:17:53,561
(Yu Jin and Ji Seung begin to show
their emotions over Si Won.)
